-bacf-24b396c47d7a", "children": ["34f8a5ff-4d30-4b63-ae1d-4c6f42270451"]}, "2b553b59-116d-46b3-8830-4f28c60fdf43": {"id": "2b553b59-116d-46b3-8830-4f28c60fdf43", "message": {"id": "2b553b59-116d-46b3-8830-4f28c60fdf43", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189741.336663, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "thoughts", "thoughts": [{"summary": "Resolvendo conflitos e erros", "content": "Parece que o usu\u00e1rio est\u00e1 lidando com diversos problemas, incluindo conflitos de chave GPG e falta de espa\u00e7o. Minha sugest\u00e3o seria remover arquivos duplicados de `.list`, manter apenas os arquivos `.sources`. Para resolver a chave ausente, o pacote `termux-keyring` pode ser \u00fatil, especialmente para atualizar as chaves. Se o problema de espa\u00e7o persistir, ser\u00e1 necess\u00e1rio liberar armazenamento.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Ajustando Termux e corrigindo erros", "content": "Em rela\u00e7\u00e3o ao Termux, a melhor abordagem seria desabilitar os reposit\u00f3rios x11 e root ou atribuir a chave \"Signed-By\" para `termux.gpg` e rodar o `termux-keyring refresh`. O erro com o `awk` acontece porque ele n\u00e3o est\u00e1 dispon\u00edvel no Termux, ent\u00e3o usamos `gawk` ou `mawk`. Tamb\u00e9m, o aviso \"n\u00e3o h\u00e1 espa\u00e7o\" indica falta de configura\u00e7\u00e3o do servi\u00e7o, mas pode ser resolvido depois.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Gerenciando espa\u00e7o e aperfei\u00e7oando o script", "content": "\u00c9 preciso adicionar uma verifica\u00e7\u00e3o de espa\u00e7o livre antes da ingest\u00e3o de arquivos e parar o processo quando o espa\u00e7o estiver baixo. J\u00e1 implementamos uma checagem antes do \u00edndice, mas agora vamos configurar um limite para fallback, movendo os arquivos em vez de copiar. Quanto ao script, vamos instalar `gawk` e ajustar as configura\u00e7\u00f5es de chaves no Termux.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Ajustando o Termux para economizar espa\u00e7o", "content": "Para gerenciar o espa\u00e7o no dispositivo e prevenir falhas, podemos adicionar um comando que checke o espa\u00e7o livre e pare se for abaixo de 500MB. Se necess\u00e1rio, podemos criar links simb\u00f3licos em vez de copiar arquivos grandes. Tamb\u00e9m, vou fornecer comandos para limpar duplica\u00e7\u00f5es nos arquivos de fontes do Termux e atualizar as chaves.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}], "source_analysis_msg_id": "ba08bfa2-1d74-4de5-a17f-a06820007cae"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "citations": [], "content_references": [], "classifier_response": "default", "skip_reasoning_title": "Pular", "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "9751455c69ef3652-FLN", "message_type": "variant", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "82edb4dc-0b2a-481d-95fc-88d18d921aaa", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "82edb4dc-0b2a-481d-95fc-88d18d921aaa", "children": ["fb7085d5-8c21-4a32-8c8b-e40163959664"]}, "25548c3c-ac02-4e45-b55e-9d162dcc7e12": {"id": "25548c3c-ac02-4e45-b55e-9d162dcc7e12", "message": {"id": "25548c3c-ac02-4e45-b55e-9d162dcc7e12", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189744.765581, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "thoughts", "thoughts": [{"summary": "Propondo corre\u00e7\u00f5es para erros", "content": "Eu preciso lidar com alguns erros, como conflitos com a chave APT Signed-By, falta de chaves no x11/root e duplica\u00e7\u00e3o de arquivos .list e .sources. Tamb\u00e9m achei um problema com o pacote awk no Termux, que deve ser substitu\u00eddo pelo pacote gawk. Vou sugerir comandos de corre\u00e7\u00e3o e uma atualiza\u00e7\u00e3o para o script.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Ajustando reposit\u00f3rios e espa\u00e7o em disco", "content": "A melhor abordagem seria remover reposit\u00f3rios de root e x11, ou ajustar a chave Signed-By para o mesmo arquivo termux.gpg. Caso contr\u00e1rio, desabilitar temporariamente esses reposit\u00f3rios pode resolver o erro do apt. Tamb\u00e9m vou liberar espa\u00e7o, movendo arquivos grandes e ajustando configura\u00e7\u00f5es para evitar c\u00f3pias desnecess\u00e1rias de arquivos grandes.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Ajustando script e comandos", "content": "Precisamos criar um patch para corrigir a fun\u00e7\u00e3o fix-apt. Isso incluir\u00e1 a remo\u00e7\u00e3o de arquivos *.list antigos e garantir que apenas .sources sejam usados. Vou tamb\u00e9m ajustar a instala\u00e7\u00e3o, removendo o pacote 'awk' (j\u00e1 que Termux usa 'gawk'). Al\u00e9m disso, adicionar um alerta de espa\u00e7o baixo e um comando para mover grandes arquivos da pasta $HOME para o /sdcard.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Corrigindo conflitos e liberando espa\u00e7o", "content": "Vou criar um conjunto de comandos r\u00e1pidos para resolver conflitos, liberar espa\u00e7o e atualizar o script. As etapas incluem limpar listas duplicadas, desabilitar reposit\u00f3rios, atualizar chaves, e limpar cache. Tamb\u00e9m vou fornecer comandos para mover arquivos grandes para liberar espa\u00e7o, mantendo tudo bem conciso e em blocos de c\u00f3digo.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}], "source_analysis_msg_id": "0196a435-e38c-4874-825d-09922df15417"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "citations": [], "content_references": [], "classifier_response": "default", "skip_reasoning_title": "Pular", "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "975145951dfd3652-FLN", "message_type": "variant", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "c8038e87-0bfa-4950-a847-b595760c18b5", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "c8038e87-0bfa-4950-a847-b595760c18b5", "children": ["927d2a8d-e5ef-45f1-926d-954281c76cda"]}, "d369cb7a-8780-4311-8ad4-0790083f5957": {"id": "d369cb7a-8780-4311-8ad4-0790083f5957", "message": {"id": "d369cb7a-8780-4311-8ad4-0790083f5957", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189931.985238, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "thoughts", "thoughts": [{"summary": "Considerando o gerenciamento de espa\u00e7o", "content": "Devemos adicionar uma verifica\u00e7\u00e3o de espa\u00e7o livre no sub_ingest, como checar o espa\u00e7o livre e o limite m\u00ednimo. Podemos tamb\u00e9m optar por criar links simb\u00f3licos em vez de copiar, para evitar o aumento do uso de armazenamento. No Android/Termux, isso pode significar criar links de /sdcard para o INBOX, economizando espa\u00e7o.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Corrigindo APT e fontes", "content": "Devemos corrigir a quest\u00e3o do APT, removendo arquivos antigos e configurando as fontes corretamente. Para isso, listamos as fontes, removemos duplicatas e garantimos que as linhas \"Signed-By\" apontem para o arquivo correto. Tamb\u00e9m podemos precisar reinstalar o keyring do Termux e atualizar o APT, verificando se as chaves s\u00e3o compat\u00edveis.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Ajustando fontes e chaves APT", "content": "Parece que o problema se deve a arquivos antigos e a falta de chave \"Signed-By\" para o root e x11. Precisamos remover os arquivos `.list` antigos e corrigir as duplica\u00e7\u00f5es de configura\u00e7\u00f5es. Tamb\u00e9m podemos remover o `termux-main.gpg` e ajustar a fun\u00e7\u00e3o `sub_fix_apt` para limpar agressivamente as fontes e configura\u00e7\u00f5es.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Ajustando sub_ingest e apt", "content": "Vou ajustar o sub_ingest para o modo de link e adicionar os limiares necess\u00e1rios. Para o servi\u00e7o headsupd, vamos criar os arquivos de supervis\u00e3o e resolver o aviso causado pela execu\u00e7\u00e3o cedo do 'sv up'. Tamb\u00e9m vamos remover 'awk' da lista de pacotes, mantendo apenas 'gawk', e incluir verifica\u00e7\u00f5es de espa\u00e7o.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Atualiza\u00e7\u00e3o do script e melhorias", "content": "Vamos gerar o script 'BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh', que inclui melhorias como redirecionamento de logs para o SD quando o espa\u00e7o estiver baixo e implementa\u00e7\u00e3o de ingest\u00e3o via symlink para otimizar o uso de espa\u00e7o. Al\u00e9m disso, ajustaremos a limpeza agressiva do APT e removeremos pacotes desnecess\u00e1rios como 'awk', com ajustes nos servi\u00e7os e melhorias no \u00edndice, incluindo a execu\u00e7\u00e3o de comandos 'find -L'.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}], "source_analysis_msg_id": "21bed957-827f-475e-9e49-a8a35bb3f18e"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "citations": [], "content_references": [], "classifier_response": "default", "skip_reasoning_title": "Pular", "request_id": "97514a280bcd3652-FLN", "message_type": "variant", "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "requested_model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "c8e438b0-30bd-44cc-b6eb-1b94aae8a9f6", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "c8e438b0-30bd-44cc-b6eb-1b94aae8a9f6", "children": ["8dc5913a-519b-45d1-9e9d-fce73c4f7796"]}, "34f8a5ff-4d30-4b63-ae1d-4c6f42270451": {"id": "34f8a5ff-4d30-4b63-ae1d-4c6f42270451", "message": {"id": "34f8a5ff-4d30-4b63-ae1d-4c6f42270451", "author": {"role": "system", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189726.8562417, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": [""]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"is_contextual_answers_system_message": true, "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true, "command": "prompt", "contextual_answers_message_type": "sources_and_filters_prompt", "request_id": "9751452848b43652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "e5f7d898-90d9-4027-ae42-69185648a9ae", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "e5f7d898-90d9-4027-ae42-69185648a9ae", "children": ["f7718a89-8c43-4443-85e7-00b67aaf7b22"]}, "fb7085d5-8c21-4a32-8c8b-e40163959664": {"id": "fb7085d5-8c21-4a32-8c8b-e40163959664", "message": {"id": "fb7085d5-8c21-4a32-8c8b-e40163959664", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189777.930663, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "reasoning_recap", "content": "Pensou por 43s"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "reasoning_ended", "finished_duration_sec": 43, "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "9751455c69ef3652-FLN", "message_type": "variant", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "2b553b59-116d-46b3-8830-4f28c60fdf43", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "2b553b59-116d-46b3-8830-4f28c60fdf43", "children": ["9f203f61-18dd-4f25-9875-0d9267aafaed"]}, "927d2a8d-e5ef-45f1-926d-954281c76cda": {"id": "927d2a8d-e5ef-45f1-926d-954281c76cda", "message": {"id": "927d2a8d-e5ef-45f1-926d-954281c76cda", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189771.787994, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "reasoning_recap", "content": "Pensou por 31s"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "reasoning_ended", "finished_duration_sec": 31, "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "975145951dfd3652-FLN", "message_type": "variant", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "25548c3c-ac02-4e45-b55e-9d162dcc7e12", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "25548c3c-ac02-4e45-b55e-9d162dcc7e12", "children": ["50b4a104-3761-436e-bc5f-fbf050ebd132"]}, "8dc5913a-519b-45d1-9e9d-fce73c4f7796": {"id": "8dc5913a-519b-45d1-9e9d-fce73c4f7796", "message": {"id": "8dc5913a-519b-45d1-9e9d-fce73c4f7796", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756190007.382635, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "reasoning_recap", "content": "Pensou por 1m 21s"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "reasoning_ended", "finished_duration_sec": 81, "request_id": "97514a280bcd3652-FLN", "message_type": "variant", "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "requested_model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "d369cb7a-8780-4311-8ad4-0790083f5957", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "d369cb7a-8780-4311-8ad4-0790083f5957", "children": ["ba0ea5e6-1d8c-4380-be34-e1228c328a00"]}, "f7718a89-8c43-4443-85e7-00b67aaf7b22": {"id": "f7718a89-8c43-4443-85e7-00b67aaf7b22", "message": {"id": "f7718a89-8c43-4443-85e7-00b67aaf7b22", "author": {"role": "tool", "name": "file_search", "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189727.4561207, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "tether_browsing_display", "result": "", "summary": "", "assets": null, "tether_id": null}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 0.0, "metadata": {"command": "spinner", "status": "running", "reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true, "classifier_response": "default", "request_id": "9751452848b43652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "34f8a5ff-4d30-4b63-ae1d-4c6f42270451", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "34f8a5ff-4d30-4b63-ae1d-4c6f42270451", "children": ["a21a0303-5d9c-420d-a223-3534cfafb1cd"]}, "9f203f61-18dd-4f25-9875-0d9267aafaed": {"id": "9f203f61-18dd-4f25-9875-0d9267aafaed", "message": {"id": "9f203f61-18dd-4f25-9875-0d9267aafaed", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189734.528534, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["Bora consertar **AGORA no telefone**, sem abrir editor, s\u00f3 colando comandos. Pelos logs, h\u00e1 4 problemas:\n\n1) **APT duplicado + Signed-By conflitando** (`.list` + `.sources`)  \n2) **NO_PUBKEY** em `root`/`x11`  \n3) `awk` n\u00e3o existe em Termux (use `gawk`)  \n4) **Sem espa\u00e7o** \u2192 `cp` falha no `ingest` (precisamos trocar por **symlink**)\n\nAbaixo vai um **hotfix cir\u00fargico**, em 4 blocos.\n\n---\n\n## 1) APT \u2014 limpar duplicados e deixar UMA chave\n\n> Remove `.list` antigos, deixa s\u00f3 `.sources` com **Signed-By: termux.gpg**, e **desabilita root/x11** at\u00e9 a chave estar ok.\n\n```bash\nPREFIX=\"/data/data/com.termux/files/usr\"\nAPT=\"$PREFIX/etc/apt\"; SRC=\"$APT/sources.list.d\"; TRUST=\"$APT/trusted.gpg.d\"\n\n# backup m\u00ednimo\nmkdir -p \"$APT/bak_fix\"; cp -a \"$SRC\" \"$TRUST\" \"$APT/bak_fix\"/ 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# REMOVER .list antigos (causam 'Target Packages ... configured multiple times')\nrm -f \"$APT/sources.list\"\nrm -f \"$SRC/\"*.list 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# garantir keyring \u00fanico\nrm -f \"$TRUST/termux-main.gpg\" 2>/dev/null || true\npkg reinstall -y termux-keyring || pkg install -y termux-keyring || true\n\n# limpar caches\napt-get clean || true\nrm -rf \"$APT/lists/\"* 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# habilitar SOMENTE termux-main por enquanto (root/x11 OFF)\ncat > \"$SRC/termux-main.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://packages.termux.dev/apt/termux-main\nSuites: stable\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\nrm -f \"$SRC/x11.sources\" \"$SRC/root.sources\" 2>/dev/null || true\n\napt update || true\n```\n\n> Quando quisermos x11/root depois, a gente reativa e verifica chaves \u2014 por ora **deixa s\u00f3 termux-main** est\u00e1vel.\n\n---\n\n## 2) Corrigir `init` (remover `awk`) e recarregar script\n\n> Seu Termux j\u00e1 tem `gawk`; o pacote `awk` n\u00e3o existe. Trocarei via `sed`.\n\n```bash\n# remove \" awk \" da lista de pacotes no teu script\nsed -i 's/ gawk awk / gawk /' ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh\nbash -n ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh && echo \"syntax OK\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3) Parar de COPIAR (enche o /data) e usar **symlinks** no INBOX\n\n> Trocaremos o `sub_ingest` para **criar links simb\u00f3licos** em `INBOX/` em vez de copiar. Isso n\u00e3o ocupa espa\u00e7o relevante e evita \u201cNo space left on device\u201d.\n\nCole o patch abaixo (ele **substitui** a fun\u00e7\u00e3o inteira):\n\n```bash\ncat > ~/.tmp_ingest_fix.sh <<'SH'\nfix_func(){\nawk '\n  BEGIN{ skip=1 }\n  /^sub_ingest\\(\\)\\{/ { print; skip=0; print \"  say \\\"[INGEST] varrendo fontes\u2026\\\"\"; print \"  local globs=\\\"${SCAN_GLOBS:-/sdcard/Download/* /sdcard/*}\\\"\"; print \"  local count=0 dest f\"; print \"  mkdir -p \\\"$INBOX\\\"\"; print \"\"; print \"  shopt -s nullglob dotglob\"; print \"  for pattern in $globs; do\"; print \"    if [ -d \\\"$pattern\\\" ]; then\"; print \"      while IFS= read -r -d \\\"\\\" f; do\"; print \"        [ -f \\\"$f\\\" ] || continue\"; print \"        dest=\\\"$INBOX/$(basename \\\"$f\\\")\\\"\"; print \"        ln -sfn -- \\\"$f\\\" \\\"$dest\\\" && count=$((count+1)) || true\"; print \"      done < <(find \\\"$pattern\\\" -maxdepth 1 -type f -print0 2>/dev/null)\"; print \"    else\"; print \"      for f in $pattern; do\"; print \"        [ -f \\\"$f\\\" ] || continue\"; print \"        dest=\\\"$INBOX/$(basename \\\"$f\\\")\\\"\"; print \"        ln -sfn -- \\\"$f\\\" \\\"$dest\\\" && count=$((count+1)) || true\"; print \"      done\"; print \"    fi\"; print \"  done\"; print \"  shopt -u nullglob dotglob\"; print \"  say \\\"[INGEST] $count links \u2192 $INBOX\\\"\"; print \"}\"; next }\n  /^}\\s*$/ && skip==0 { skip=1; next }\n  skip==1 { print }\n' ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh > ~/.BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh.new\nmv ~/.BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh.new ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh\n}\nfix_func\nSH\nbash ~/.tmp_ingest_fix.sh && rm -f ~/.tmp_ingest_fix.sh\nbash -n ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh && echo \"ingest -> symlink OK\"\n```\n\n> Resultado: `INBOX/arquivo.ext` vira **link** para `/sdcard/.../arquivo.ext`. O `index` continua funcionando igual (ele segue link e l\u00ea o arquivo real).\n\n---\n\n## 4) (Opcional) consertar o servi\u00e7o heads-up \u201csupervise/ok\u201d\n\n> Esse aviso aparece quando o runit ainda n\u00e3o criou `supervise/`. Crie e suba com calma:\n\n```bash\nSVC=\"$PREFIX/var/service/heads-up-cleaner\"\nmkdir -p \"$SVC\"\ncat > \"$SVC/run\" <<'R'\n#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash\nexec ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh headsupd start\nR\nchmod +x \"$SVC/run\"\nsv down heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true\nsleep 1\nsv up heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true\nsv status heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true\n```\n\n> Se preferir, d\u00e1 para iniciar direto sem servi\u00e7o: `~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh headsupd start`.\n\n---\n\n# Teste r\u00e1pido (sequ\u00eancia enxuta)\n\n```bash\n# APT saneado\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh fix-apt\n\n# deps b\u00e1sicos e servi\u00e7os\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh init\n\n# (opcional) ajustar Android 14, gera adb_once.sh\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh tune\n\n# pipeline com ingest \u2192 agora s\u00f3 symlink, sem ocupar espa\u00e7o\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh run\n```\n\nSe ainda faltar espa\u00e7o para logs, d\u00e1 um al\u00edvio r\u00e1pido:\n\n```bash\n# ver o que pesa em $HOME (top 30)\ndu -ah ~ 2>/dev/null | sort -hr | head -30\n\n# limpar caches do apt e pacotes baixados\napt-get clean || true\nrm -rf \"$PREFIX/var/cache\"/* 2>/dev/null || true\n```\n\n---\n\n## Sobre x11/root e NO_PUBKEY\n\nQuando quiser reativar:\n\n```bash\ncat > \"$SRC/x11.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://x11-packages.termux.net\nSuites: x11\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n\ncat > \"$SRC/root.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://root-packages.termux.net\nSuites: root\nComponents: stable\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n\napt update\n```\n\nSe ainda acusar `NO_PUBKEY`, mantenha desativado (remova os `.sources`) ou reinstale `termux-keyring` e repita `apt update`. O essencial (termux-main) j\u00e1 fica \u00edntegro.\n\n---\n\nSe quiser, eu empacoto essas mudan\u00e7as numa **vers\u00e3o v7_mod2** completa via `cat <<'SH'` (arquivo inteiro de novo) \u2014 mas como teu espa\u00e7o est\u00e1 cr\u00edtico, preferi **hotfix minimalista** e sem c\u00f3pias de arquivo."]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": true, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"citations": [], "content_references": [], "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "9751455c69ef3652-FLN", "message_type": "variant", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "fb7085d5-8c21-4a32-8c8b-e40163959664", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": "final"}, "parent": "fb7085d5-8c21-4a32-8c8b-e40163959664", "children": []}, "50b4a104-3761-436e-bc5f-fbf050ebd132": {"id": "50b4a104-3761-436e-bc5f-fbf050ebd132", "message": {"id": "50b4a104-3761-436e-bc5f-fbf050ebd132", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189740.085505, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["Beleza \u2014 vi tudo que aconteceu no teu Termux. Tr\u00eas coisas estouraram ao mesmo tempo:\n\n1) **APT \u201cmodded\u201d** ficou com **fontes duplicadas** (`.list` + `.sources`) e **chaves conflitantes** (`termux.gpg` vs `termux-main.gpg`).  \n2) **Reposit\u00f3rios root/x11** sem chave (NO_PUBKEY `1584981E6CDDB22D`).  \n3) **Sem espa\u00e7o em disco** \u2192 `cp: No space left on device`, at\u00e9 o log travou.\n\nVou te dar **(A) corre\u00e7\u00e3o imediata** pra colar no terminal e destravar, **(B) limpeza/park de arquivos grandes**, e **(C) patches do script** que consertam o que gerou o erro (\u201cawk\u201d inexistente no Termux, guardas de espa\u00e7o antes de copiar/indexar, e um `prune`).\n\n---\n\n## (A) Corre\u00e7\u00e3o imediata do APT (cola tudo)\n\n```bash\n# 1) Remover listas antigas que duplicam as fontes (deixa s\u00f3 *.sources)\nPREFIX=\"/data/data/com.termux/files/usr\"\nAPT=\"$PREFIX/etc/apt\"; SRC=\"$APT/sources.list.d\"; TRUST=\"$APT/trusted.gpg.d\"\n\nrm -f \"$SRC/termux-main.list\" \"$SRC/x11.list\" \"$SRC/root.list\" 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# 2) Usar UMA \u00fanica chave (termux.gpg) e remover a conflitante\nrm -f \"$TRUST/termux-main.gpg\" 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# 3) Reinstalar o keyring e limpar cache de listas\npkg reinstall -y termux-keyring || pkg install -y termux-keyring || true\napt-get clean || true\nrm -rf \"$APT/lists/\"* 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# 4) Se voc\u00ea N\u00c3O precisa de root/x11 agora, desabilita pra simplificar:\n[ -f \"$SRC/x11.sources\" ] && mv \"$SRC/x11.sources\" \"$SRC/x11.sources.disabled\"\n[ -f \"$SRC/root.sources\" ] && mv \"$SRC/root.sources\" \"$SRC/root.sources.disabled\"\n\n# 5) Recria APENAS a fonte principal com Signed-By \u00fanico\ncat > \"$SRC/termux-main.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://packages.termux.dev/apt/termux-main\nSuites: stable\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n\n# 6) Atualiza\napt update\n```\n\n> Se voc\u00ea **precisar mesmo** de `x11`/`root` depois, a gente reabilita e injeta a chave espec\u00edfica \u2014 por enquanto, o objetivo \u00e9 **parar o erro** e permitir `pkg install`.\n\n---\n\n## (B) Espa\u00e7o: limpar, parquear e respirar\n\nVoc\u00ea ficou sem espa\u00e7o durante o `ingest`. Vamos liberar e evitar repetir:\n\n```bash\n# 1) Ver espa\u00e7o\ndf -h \"$HOME\"\n\n# 2) Limpeza de caches\napt-get clean || true\nrm -rf \"$PREFIX/var/cache\"/* 2>/dev/null || true\nrm -rf \"$HOME/.cache\"/* 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# 3) Park dos arquivos grandes para o SD (n\u00e3o perde nada)\nmkdir -p /sdcard/Download/FCEA_park\n# move > 200 MB do $HOME (com relat\u00f3rio)\nfind \"$HOME\" -type f -size +200M -print -exec mv -f {} /sdcard/Download/FCEA_park/ \\;\n\n# 4) Esvaziar INBOX do pipeline para recome\u00e7ar mais leve\nrm -rf \"$HOME/FCEA_OMEGA/data/inbox\"/*\n```\n\nDepois rode de novo s\u00f3 **init** e **run** (o `fix-apt` voc\u00ea j\u00e1 fez acima):\n\n```bash\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh init\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh run\n```\n\n---\n\n## (C) Patches do teu `BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh`\n\n1) **Remover \u201cawk\u201d** da lista de pacotes (no Termux n\u00e3o existe `awk` como pacote; use `gawk`).  \n2) **Guardas de espa\u00e7o antes do ingest e do run** (n\u00e3o copia nada se < 200MB livres).  \n3) **Subcomando `prune`** pra limpar logs antigos, INBOX e \u00edndices quando o espa\u00e7o apertar.  \n4) **Fix do APT refor\u00e7ado**: apaga `.list`, remove `termux-main.gpg`, permite opcionalmente desabilitar `x11`/`root`.\n\n### Patch r\u00e1pido \u2014 cole para REGERAR o script com ajustes\n\n```bash\ncat > ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh <<'SH'\n#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash\nset -Eeuo pipefail\n\nTS(){ date '+%F %T'; }\nsay(){ printf '%s %s\\n' \"$(TS)\" \"$*\"; }\n\nPREFIX=\"/data/data/com.termux/files/usr\"\nAPT=\"$PREFIX/etc/apt\"; SRC=\"$APT/sources.list.d\"; TRUST=\"$APT/trusted.gpg.d\"\n\nBASE=\"${BASE:-$HOME/FCEA_OMEGA}\"\nETC=\"$BASE/etc\"; BIN=\"$BASE/bin\"; DATA=\"$BASE/data\"; OUT=\"$BASE/out\"; BAK=\"$BASE/backups\"\nINBOX=\"$DATA/inbox\"; INDEX=\"$BASE/index\"\nLOGDIR=\"$HOME/rafaelia_logs\"; mkdir -p \"$LOGDIR\" \"$ETC\" \"$BIN\" \"$DATA\" \"$OUT\" \"$BAK\" \"$INBOX\" \"$INDEX\"\nLOG=\"$LOGDIR/uno_v7_mod.log\"; exec > >(tee -a \"$LOG\") 2>&1\nsay \"\u25b6 UNO v7_mod start\"\n\nneed(){ command -v \"$1\" >/dev/null 2>&1 || { say \"[MISS] $1\"; return 1; }; }\nfree_mb(){ df -Pm \"$HOME\" | awk 'NR==2{print $4}'; }\nsha(){ sha256sum \"$1\" 2>/dev/null | awk '{print $1}'; }\n\nsub_fix_apt(){\n  say \"[APT] normalizando reposit\u00f3rios\u2026\"\n  local back=\"$APT/backup_fix_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)\"; mkdir -p \"$back\"\n  cp -a \"$SRC\" \"$back/\" 2>/dev/null || true; cp -a \"$TRUST\" \"$back/\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  say \"[backup] fontes/keyring \u2192 $back\"\n\n  # zera duplica\u00e7\u00f5es e conflito de chave\n  rm -f \"$SRC/termux-main.list\" \"$SRC/x11.list\" \"$SRC/root.list\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  rm -f \"$TRUST/termux-main.gpg\" 2>/dev/null || true\n\n  pkg reinstall -y termux-keyring || pkg install -y termux-keyring || true\n  apt-get clean || true; rm -rf \"$APT/lists/\"* 2>/dev/null || true\n\n  # se quiser simplificar, desabilite x11/root neste momento:\n  [ -f \"$SRC/x11.sources\" ] && mv \"$SRC/x11.sources\" \"$SRC/x11.sources.disabled\"\n  [ -f \"$SRC/root.sources\" ] && mv \"$SRC/root.sources\" \"$SRC/root.sources.disabled\"\n\n  cat > \"$SRC/termux-main.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://packages.termux.dev/apt/termux-main\nSuites: stable\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n\n  apt update\n  say \"[APT] ok.\"\n}\n\nsub_init(){\n  say \"[INIT] deps + servi\u00e7os\u2026\"\n  pkg install -y termux-services || true\n  mkdir -p \"$PREFIX/var/service\" || true\n  sv-enable crond 2>/dev/null || true\n  sv up crond 2>/dev/null || true\n\n  # IMPORTANTE: sem 'awk' (n\u00e3o existe pacote awk no Termux)\n  pkg install -y coreutils findutils tar gzip xz-utils zip unzip p7zip \\\n                 gawk sed grep ripgrep sqlite sox ffmpeg util-linux \\\n                 python nodejs-lts file || true\n\n  command -v termux-setup-storage >/dev/null 2>&1 && termux-setup-storage || true\n  grep -q 'umask 077' \"$HOME/.bashrc\" 2>/dev/null || echo 'umask 077'>>\"$HOME/.bashrc\"\n  chmod -R go-rwx \"$BASE\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  say \"[INIT] ok. BASE=$BASE\"\n}\n\nsub_tune(){\n  say \"[TUNE] Android 14\u2026\"\n  sub_init\n  local is_root=0; command -v su >/dev/null 2>&1 && su -c id | grep -q \"uid=0\" && is_root=1 || true\n  local ADB=\"$HOME/adb_once.sh\"\n  cat > \"$ADB\" <<'ADB'\n#!/system/bin/sh\ncmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux\ncmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux.api 2>/dev/null || true\nappops set com.termux RUN_ANY_IN_BACKGROUND allow 2>/dev/null || true\nappops set com.termux WAKE_LOCK allow 2>/dev/null || true\nsettings put global app_standby_enabled 0 2>/dev/null || true\nsettings put global heads_up_notifications_enabled 0 2>/dev/null || true\nADB\n  chmod +x \"$ADB\"; say \"[TUNE] gerado $ADB (use via ADB se sem root).\"\n  if [ \"$is_root\" -eq 1 ]; then\n    su -c \"cmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux\" || true\n    su -c \"cmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux.api\" || true\n    su -c \"appops set com.termux RUN_ANY_IN_BACKGROUND allow\" || true\n    su -c \"appops set com.termux WAKE_LOCK allow\" || true\n    su -c \"settings put global heads_up_notifications_enabled 0\" || true\n    su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 1\" || true; sleep 0.2; su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 0\" || true\n    say \"[TUNE] ajustes root aplicados.\"\n  fi\n}\n\nsub_headsupd(){\n  local action=\"${1:-status}\"\n  local SVC=\"$PREFIX/var/service/heads-up-cleaner\"\n  case \"$action\" in\n    start)\n      mkdir -p \"$SVC\"\n      cat > \"$SVC/run\" <<'R'\n#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash\nset -Eeuo pipefail\nLOG=\"$HOME/rafaelia_logs/heads_up_cleaner.log\"; mkdir -p \"${LOG%/*}\"\nis_root(){ command -v su >/dev/null 2>&1 && su -c id | grep -q 'uid=0'; }\nif ! is_root; then\n  echo \"$(date '+%F %T') [WARN] sem root: efeito limitado\" >> \"$LOG\"\n  while :; do sleep 30; done\nfi\nwhile :; do\n  su -c \"cmd statusbar collapse-panels\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 1\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 0.2\n  su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 0\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 3\ndone\nR\n      chmod +x \"$SVC/run\"\n      sv up heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true\n      sv-enable heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true\n      say \"[HUN] daemon iniciado.\"\n      ;;\n    stop)   sv down heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true; sv-disable heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true; say \"[HUN] parado.\";;\n    status) sv status heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || { say \"[HUN] servi\u00e7o ausente\"; } ;;\n    *)      say \"uso: $0 headsupd {start|stop|status}\";;\n  esac\n}\n\nsub_ingest(){\n  say \"[INGEST] varrendo fontes\u2026\"\n  local free=\"$(free_mb)\"; if [ \"${free:-0}\" -lt 400 ]; then say \"[INGEST] abort: livre ${free}MB < 400MB\"; return 0; fi\n  local globs=\"${SCAN_GLOBS:-/sdcard/Download/* /sdcard/*}\"\n  local count=0 dest f; mkdir -p \"$INBOX\"\n  shopt -s nullglob dotglob\n  for pattern in $globs; do\n    if [ -d \"$pattern\" ]; then\n      while IFS= read -r -d '' f; do\n        [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n        dest=\"$INBOX/$(basename \"$f\")\"\n        if [ ! -e \"$dest\" ]; then cp -n -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true; fi\n      done < <(find \"$pattern\" -maxdepth 1 -type f -print0 2>/dev/null)\n    else\n      for f in $pattern; do\n        [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n        dest=\"$INBOX/$(basename \"$f\")\"\n        if [ ! -e \"$dest\" ]; then cp -n -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true; fi\n      done\n    fi\n  done\n  shopt -u nullglob dotglob\n  say \"[INGEST] $count novos \u2192 $INBOX\"\n}\n\nsub_index(){\n  say \"[INDEX] cat\u00e1logo profundo\u2026\"\n  local free=\"$(free_mb)\"; [ \"${free:-0}\" -lt 200 ] && { say \"[INDEX] abort: livre ${free}MB < 200MB\"; return 0; }\n  local CSV=\"$INDEX/index.csv\"; local JSON=\"$INDEX/index.jsonl\"; local SQL=\"$INDEX/index.sqlite\"; local LOGI=\"$INDEX/index.log\"\n  mkdir -p \"$INDEX\"; : > \"$JSON\"; : > \"$CSV\"; echo 'path,size_bytes,sha256,kind,extra,json' > \"$CSV\"\n  need sqlite3 || pkg install -y sqlite || true\n  sqlite3 \"$SQL\" 'PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL; CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS files(path TEXT PRIMARY KEY,size_bytes INTEGER,sha256 TEXT,kind TEXT,extra TEXT,json TEXT);'\n  list_zip(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport zipfile,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  with zipfile.ZipFile(p,'r') as z:\n    infos=[{'name':i.filename,'size':i.file_size,'comp':i.compress_size} for i in z.infolist() if not i.is_dir()]\n    print(json.dumps({'entries':len(infos),'top':infos[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  list_tar(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport tarfile,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  with tarfile.open(p,'r:*') as t:\n    names=[m.name for m in t.getmembers() if m.isfile()]\n    print(json.dumps({'entries':len(names),'top':names[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  list_sqlite(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport sqlite3,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  con=sqlite3.connect(p); cur=con.cursor()\n  cur.execute(\"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table'\"); tabs=[r[0] for r in cur.fetchall()]\n  info={}\n  for t in tabs[:25]:\n    try: cur.execute(f\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM '{t}'\"); info[t]=cur.fetchone()[0]\n    except Exception as e: info[t]=str(e)\n  print(json.dumps({'tables':len(tabs),'counts':info,'sample':tabs[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  summ(){ head -n \"${2:-12}\" \"$1\" 2>/dev/null | tr -d '\\r' | sed 's/\"/'\\''/g'; }\n  echo \"$(TS) [START] $INBOX \u2192 $INDEX\" | tee -a \"$LOGI\"\n  while IFS= read -r -d '' f; do\n    size=$(stat -c %s \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || stat -f %z \"$f\"); h=$(sha \"$f\" || true)\n    ext=\"${f##*.}\"; ext=\"${ext,,}\"\n    case \"$ext\" in\n      zip) extra=$(list_zip \"$f\"); kind=\"zip\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"zip\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$extra\");;\n      tar|gz|tgz|bz2|xz) extra=$(list_tar \"$f\"); kind=\"tar\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"tar\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$extra\");;\n      db|sqlite|sqlite3) extra=$(list_sqlite \"$f\"); kind=\"sqlite\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"sqlite\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$extra\");;\n      sh|py|js|json|md|txt|cfg|ini|yml|yaml) preview=$(summ \"$f\" 12 | sed 's/[[:cntrl:]]//g'); kind=\"text\"; extra=\"preview\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"text\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"preview\":\"%s\"}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$preview\");;\n      *) kind=\"$(file -b --mime-type \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"?\")\"; extra=\"\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"%s\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\"}' \"$f\" \"$kind\" \"$size\" \"$h\");;\n    esac\n    printf '%s,%s,%s,\"%s\",\"%s\",\"%s\"\\n' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$kind\" \"${extra//\\\"/\\\"\\\"}\" \"${json//\\\"/\\\"\\\"}\" >> \"$CSV\"\n    printf '%s\\n' \"$json\" >> \"$JSON\"\n    sqlite3 \"$SQL\" \"INSERT OR REPLACE INTO files VALUES(?,?,?,?,?,?);\" \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$kind\" \"$extra\" \"$json\"\n  done < <(find \"$INBOX\" -type f -print0 2>/dev/null)\n  echo \"$(TS) [OK] CSV:$CSV JSONL:$JSON SQLITE:$SQL\" | tee -a \"$LOGI\"\n}\n\nsub_backup(){\n  say \"[BK] empacotando\u2026\"\n  local stamp=\"$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)\"; local bundle=\"$BAK/state_$stamp.zip\"; local mtmp=\"$OUT/manifest_runtime.json\"\n  cat > \"$mtmp\" <<JSON\n{\"run_at\":\"$(TS)\",\"base\":\"$BASE\",\"schema\":1,\n \"paridade\":\"par\",\"tesseract_hyperformas\":\"1 tesseract + 4 hyperformas\",\n \"chave_simbiotica\":\"Fibonacci_mod + Voynich \ua66e-\u0394-\ud80c\udc80\"}\nJSON\n  ( cd \"$HOME\" && zip -qr \"$bundle\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$LOG\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$INDEX\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$OUT\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$mtmp\")\" \\\n  ) || true\n  say \"[BK] \u2192 $bundle\"\n}\n\nsub_mirror(){\n  if ! command -v rclone >/dev/null 2>&1; then say \"[SYNC] rclone ausente; pulando\"; return 0; fi\n  local conf=\"$HOME/.config/rclone/rclone.conf\"\n  if grep -q 'PREENCHER' \"$conf\" 2>/dev/null; then say \"[SYNC] rclone.conf placeholder\"; return 0; fi\n  local DST=\"VAULT:FCEA_OMEGA\"; local DATE=\"$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\"\n  say \"[SYNC] $BASE \u2192 $DST/$DATE\"\n  rclone copy \"$BASE\" \"$DST/$DATE\" --fast-list --checkers=6 --transfers=6 --tpslimit=8 --log-level INFO || true\n  say \"[SYNC] ok.\"\n}\n\nsub_prune(){\n  say \"[PRUNE] limpando logs/\u00edndices e inbox\u2026\"\n  rm -f \"$LOGDIR\"/*.log.[0-9].gz 2>/dev/null || true\n  find \"$LOGDIR\" -type f -name '*.log' -size +8M -delete 2>/dev/null || true\n  rm -rf \"$INDEX\"/* 2>/dev/null || true\n  rm -rf \"$INBOX\"/* 2>/dev/null || true\n  say \"[PRUNE] feito.\"\n}\n\nsub_run(){\n  say \"=== RUN in\u00edcio ===\"\n  local free=\"$(free_mb)\"; if [ \"${free:-0}\" -lt 600 ]; then say \"[RUN] abort: livre ${free}MB < 600MB\"; return 0; fi\n  sub_ingest; sub_index; sub_backup; sub_mirror\n  say \"=== RUN fim ===\"\n}\n\nsub_help(){\n  cat <<H\nuso: $0 <fix-apt|init|tune|headsupd {start|stop|status}|ingest|index|backup|mirror|prune|run|help>\nH\n}\n\ncmd=\"${1:-help}\"\ncase \"$cmd\" in\n  fix-apt)   sub_fix_apt;;\n  init)      sub_init;;\n  tune)      sub_tune;;\n  headsupd)  shift; sub_headsupd \"${1:-status}\";;\n  ingest)    sub_ingest;;\n  index)     sub_index;;\n  backup)    sub_backup;;\n  mirror)    sub_mirror;;\n  prune)     sub_prune;;\n  run)       sub_run;;\n  help|*)    sub_help;;\nesac\nSH\nchmod +x ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh\n```\n\n---\n\n## Resumo do que fazer agora, em ordem curta\n\n1) **Cole o bloco (A)** para consertar o APT.  \n2) **Cole o bloco (B)** para liberar espa\u00e7o.  \n3) **Cole o bloco (C)** para atualizar teu script.  \n4) Rode:\n```bash\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh init\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh run\n```\n\nSe em algum momento o espa\u00e7o voltar a ficar cr\u00edtico:\n```bash\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod.sh prune\ndf -h \"$HOME\"\n```\n\nQuer que eu tamb\u00e9m **adicione r\u00f3tulos simbi\u00f3ticos** (paridade/tesseract/hyperformas) no **nome do bundle** e como **colunas extras** no `index.sqlite`/CSV? Posso te devolver um patchzinho que j\u00e1 grava esses metadados em todas as sa\u00eddas."]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": true, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"citations": [], "content_references": [], "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "975145951dfd3652-FLN", "message_type": "variant", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "927d2a8d-e5ef-45f1-926d-954281c76cda", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": "final"}, "parent": "927d2a8d-e5ef-45f1-926d-954281c76cda", "children": []}, "ba0ea5e6-1d8c-4380-be34-e1228c328a00": {"id": "ba0ea5e6-1d8c-4380-be34-e1228c328a00", "message": {"id": "ba0ea5e6-1d8c-4380-be34-e1228c328a00", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189926.093391, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["Bora resolver TUDO no pr\u00f3prio telefone, via `cat`, do jeitinho que voc\u00ea pediu \u2014 com os consertos que seu log mostrou:\n\n- **APT modded**: limpa `.list` antigos, padroniza **um \u00fanico Signed-By** e, se o update falhar, **desabilita x11/root** automaticamente e tenta de novo.  \n- **Ingest**: sem \u201cNo space left on device\u201d. Entra em **modo link** (symlink) quando o espa\u00e7o estiver baixo e nunca tenta copiar arquiv\u00e3o \u00e0 toa.  \n- **Index**: segue symlinks (`find -L`) e continua introspec\u00e7\u00e3o ZIP/TAR/SQLite.  \n- **Logs**: se o `/data` estiver apertado, muda os logs para **/sdcard/rafaelia_logs**.  \n- **Pacotes**: remove `awk` inexistente (voc\u00ea j\u00e1 tem `gawk`).  \n- **Heads-up daemon**: inicializa\u00e7\u00e3o mais est\u00e1vel (enable \u2192 small sleep \u2192 up).\n\nCole **tudo** no Termux:\n\n```bash\ncat > ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh <<'SH'\n#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash\n# RAFAELIA \u2014 UNO v7_mod2 (Android 14 / Termux modded-friendly)\n# subcmds: fix-apt | init | tune | headsupd {start|stop|status} | ingest | index | backup | mirror | run | help\nset -Eeuo pipefail\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 util \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nTS(){ date '+%F %T'; }\nsay(){ printf '%s %s\\n' \"$(TS)\" \"$*\"; }\nneed(){ command -v \"$1\" >/dev/null 2>&1 || { say \"[MISS] $1\"; return 1; }; }\nfree_mb(){ df -Pm \"$HOME\" | awk 'NR==2{print $4}'; }\nsha(){ sha256sum \"$1\" 2>/dev/null | awk '{print $1}'; }\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 paths e logs (com fallback p/ sdcard) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nPREFIX=\"/data/data/com.termux/files/usr\"\nAPT=\"$PREFIX/etc/apt\"; SRC=\"$APT/sources.list.d\"; TRUST=\"$APT/trusted.gpg.d\"\nBASE=\"${BASE:-$HOME/FCEA_OMEGA}\"\nETC=\"$BASE/etc\"; BIN=\"$BASE/bin\"; DATA=\"$BASE/data\"; OUT=\"$BASE/out\"; BAK=\"$BASE/backups\"\nINBOX=\"$DATA/inbox\"; INDEX=\"$BASE/index\"\n\n# escolher diret\u00f3rio de log conforme espa\u00e7o\n_FREE=\"$(df -Pm \"$HOME\" | awk 'NR==2{print $4}')\"\nif [ \"${_FREE:-0}\" -lt 200 ]; then\n  LOGDIR=\"/sdcard/rafaelia_logs\"\nelse\n  LOGDIR=\"$HOME/rafaelia_logs\"\nfi\nmkdir -p \"$LOGDIR\" \"$ETC\" \"$BIN\" \"$DATA\" \"$OUT\" \"$BAK\" \"$INBOX\" \"$INDEX\"\nLOG=\"$LOGDIR/uno_v7_mod2.log\"\nexec > >(tee -a \"$LOG\") 2>&1\nsay \"\u25b6 UNO v7_mod2 start (free=${_FREE:-?}MB logdir=$LOGDIR)\"\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 fix-apt \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_fix_apt(){\n  say \"[APT] normalizando reposit\u00f3rios\u2026\"\n  local back=\"$APT/backup_fix_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)\"; mkdir -p \"$back\"\n  cp -a \"$SRC\" \"$back/\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  cp -a \"$TRUST\" \"$back/\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  say \"[backup] fontes/keyring \u2192 $back\"\n\n  # remover fontes antigas/dobradas (.list e .list.bak)\n  rm -f \"$SRC\"/*.list \"$SRC\"/*.list.bak 2>/dev/null || true\n\n  # manter s\u00f3 UMA chave\n  rm -f \"$TRUST/termux-main.gpg\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  pkg reinstall -y termux-keyring || pkg install -y termux-keyring || true\n\n  # limpar listas e sobrescrever .sources can\u00f4nicos\n  apt-get clean || true\n  rm -rf \"$APT/lists/\"* 2>/dev/null || true\n  rm -f \"$SRC/termux-main.sources\" \"$SRC/x11.sources\" \"$SRC/root.sources\" 2>/dev/null || true\n\n  cat > \"$SRC/termux-main.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://packages.termux.dev/apt/termux-main\nSuites: stable\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n  cat > \"$SRC/x11.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://x11-packages.termux.net\nSuites: x11\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n  cat > \"$SRC/root.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://root-packages.termux.net\nSuites: root\nComponents: stable\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n\n  # tenta atualizar; se falhar em root/x11, desabilita e tenta de novo\n  if ! apt update; then\n    say \"[APT] update falhou \u2014 desabilitando x11/root e tentando novamente\u2026\"\n    mv \"$SRC/x11.sources\" \"$SRC/x11.sources.off\" 2>/dev/null || true\n    mv \"$SRC/root.sources\" \"$SRC/root.sources.off\" 2>/dev/null || true\n    apt-get clean || true\n    rm -rf \"$APT/lists/\"* 2>/dev/null || true\n    apt update\n  fi\n  say \"[APT] ok.\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 init \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_init(){\n  say \"[INIT] deps + servi\u00e7os\u2026\"\n  pkg install -y termux-services || true\n  mkdir -p \"$PREFIX/var/service\" || true\n  sv-enable crond 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 1\n  sv up crond 2>/dev/null || true\n\n  # 'awk' n\u00e3o existe como pacote \u2014 use gawk\n  pkg install -y coreutils findutils tar gzip xz-utils zip unzip p7zip \\\n                 gawk sed grep ripgrep sqlite sox ffmpeg util-linux \\\n                 python nodejs-lts file || true\n\n  command -v termux-setup-storage >/dev/null 2>&1 && termux-setup-storage || true\n  grep -q 'umask 077' \"$HOME/.bashrc\" 2>/dev/null || echo 'umask 077'>>\"$HOME/.bashrc\"\n  chmod -R go-rwx \"$BASE\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  say \"[INIT] ok. BASE=$BASE\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 tune \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_tune(){\n  say \"[TUNE] Android 14\u2026\"\n  sub_init\n  local is_root=0\n  if command -v su >/dev/null 2>&1 && su -c id | grep -q \"uid=0\"; then is_root=1; fi\n\n  local ADB=\"$HOME/adb_once.sh\"\n  cat > \"$ADB\" <<'ADB'\n#!/system/bin/sh\ncmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux\ncmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux.api 2>/dev/null || true\nappops set com.termux RUN_ANY_IN_BACKGROUND allow 2>/dev/null || true\nappops set com.termux WAKE_LOCK allow 2>/dev/null || true\nsettings put global app_standby_enabled 0 2>/dev/null || true\n# heads-up pode precisar WRITE_SECURE_SETTINGS\nsettings put global heads_up_notifications_enabled 0 2>/dev/null || true\nADB\n  chmod +x \"$ADB\"\n  say \"[TUNE] gerado $ADB (use via ADB se sem root).\"\n\n  if [ \"$is_root\" -eq 1 ]; then\n    su -c \"cmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux\" || true\n    su -c \"cmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux.api\" || true\n    su -c \"appops set com.termux RUN_ANY_IN_BACKGROUND allow\" || true\n    su -c \"appops set com.termux WAKE_LOCK allow\" || true\n    su -c \"settings put global heads_up_notifications_enabled 0\" || true\n    su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 1\" || true; sleep 0.2; su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 0\" || true\n    say \"[TUNE] ajustes root aplicados.\"\n  fi\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 heads-up cleaner \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_headsupd(){\n  local action=\"${1:-status}\"\n  local SVC=\"$PREFIX/var/service/heads-up-cleaner\"\n  case \"$action\" in\n    start)\n      mkdir -p \"$SVC\"\n      cat > \"$SVC/run\" <<'R'\n#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash\nset -Eeuo pipefail\nLOG=\"$HOME/rafaelia_logs/heads_up_cleaner.log\"; mkdir -p \"${LOG%/*}\"\nis_root(){ command -v su >/dev/null 2>&1 && su -c id | grep -q 'uid=0'; }\nif ! is_root; then\n  echo \"$(date '+%F %T') [WARN] sem root: efeito limitado\" >> \"$LOG\"\n  while :; do sleep 30; done\nfi\nwhile :; do\n  su -c \"cmd statusbar collapse-panels\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 1\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 0.2\n  su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 0\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 3\ndone\nR\n      chmod +x \"$SVC/run\"\n      sv-enable heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true\n      sleep 1\n      sv up heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true\n      say \"[HUN] daemon iniciado.\"\n      ;;\n    stop)   sv down heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true; sv-disable heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true; say \"[HUN] parado.\";;\n    status) sv status heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || { say \"[HUN] servi\u00e7o ausente\"; } ;;\n    *)      say \"uso: $0 headsupd {start|stop|status}\";;\n  esac\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 ingest (auto-link p/ salvar espa\u00e7o) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_ingest(){\n  say \"[INGEST] varrendo fontes\u2026\"\n  local globs=\"${SCAN_GLOBS:-/sdcard/Download/* /sdcard/*}\"\n  local mode=\"${INGEST_MODE:-auto}\"   # auto|copy|link\n  local cutoff_mb=\"${INGEST_CUTOFF_MB:-50}\"  # acima disso for\u00e7a link em modo auto\n  local count=0 dest f\n  mkdir -p \"$INBOX\"\n\n  # decide modo pelo espa\u00e7o\n  local free=\"$(free_mb)\"\n  if [ \"$mode\" = \"auto\" ]; then\n    if [ \"${free:-0}\" -lt 512 ]; then mode=\"link\"; else mode=\"copy\"; fi\n  fi\n  say \"[INGEST] modo=$mode free=${free:-?}MB cutoff=${cutoff_mb}MB\"\n\n  shopt -s nullglob dotglob\n  for pattern in $globs; do\n    if [ -d \"$pattern\" ]; then\n      while IFS= read -r -d '' f; do\n        [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n        dest=\"$INBOX/$(basename \"$f\")\"\n        if [ ! -e \"$dest\" ]; then\n          if [ \"$mode\" = \"link\" ] || [ $(( $(stat -c %s \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || stat -f %z \"$f\") / 1024 / 1024 )) -ge \"$cutoff_mb\" ]; then\n            ln -s -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true\n          else\n            cp -n -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true\n          fi\n        fi\n      done < <(find \"$pattern\" -maxdepth 1 -type f -print0 2>/dev/null)\n    else\n      for f in $pattern; do\n        [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n        dest=\"$INBOX/$(basename \"$f\")\"\n        if [ ! -e \"$dest\" ]; then\n          if [ \"$mode\" = \"link\" ] || [ $(( $(stat -c %s \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || stat -f %z \"$f\") / 1024 / 1024 )) -ge \"$cutoff_mb\" ]; then\n            ln -s -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true\n          else\n            cp -n -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true\n          fi\n        fi\n      done\n    fi\n  done\n  shopt -u nullglob dotglob\n  say \"[INGEST] $count entradas (link/copy) \u2192 $INBOX\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 index (profundo, seguindo symlinks) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_index(){\n  say \"[INDEX] cat\u00e1logo profundo\u2026\"\n  local free=\"$(free_mb)\"; [ \"${free:-0}\" -lt 200 ] && { say \"[INDEX] abort: livre ${free}MB < 200MB\"; return 0; }\n  local CSV=\"$INDEX/index.csv\"; local JSON=\"$INDEX/index.jsonl\"; local SQL=\"$INDEX/index.sqlite\"; local LOGI=\"$INDEX/index.log\"\n  mkdir -p \"$INDEX\"; : > \"$JSON\"; : > \"$CSV\"; echo 'path,size_bytes,sha256,kind,extra,json' > \"$CSV\"\n  need sqlite3 || pkg install -y sqlite || true\n  sqlite3 \"$SQL\" 'PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL; CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS files(path TEXT PRIMARY KEY,size_bytes INTEGER,sha256 TEXT,kind TEXT,extra TEXT,json TEXT);'\n\n  list_zip(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport zipfile,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  with zipfile.ZipFile(p,'r') as z:\n    infos=[{'name':i.filename,'size':i.file_size,'comp':i.compress_size} for i in z.infolist() if not i.is_dir()]\n    print(json.dumps({'entries':len(infos),'top':infos[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  list_tar(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport tarfile,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  with tarfile.open(p,'r:*') as t:\n    names=[m.name for m in t.getmembers() if m.isfile()]\n    print(json.dumps({'entries':len(names),'top':names[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  list_sqlite(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport sqlite3,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  con=sqlite3.connect(p); cur=con.cursor()\n  cur.execute(\"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table'\"); tabs=[r[0] for r in cur.fetchall()]\n  info={}\n  for t in tabs[:25]:\n    try: cur.execute(f\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM '{t}'\"); info[t]=cur.fetchone()[0]\n    except Exception as e: info[t]=str(e)\n  print(json.dumps({'tables':len(tabs),'counts':info,'sample':tabs[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  summ(){ head -n \"${2:-12}\" \"$1\" 2>/dev/null | tr -d '\\r' | sed 's/\"/'\\''/g'; }\n\n  echo \"$(TS) [START] $INBOX \u2192 $INDEX\" | tee -a \"$LOGI\"\n  while IFS= read -r -d '' f; do\n    size=$(stat -c %s \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || stat -f %z \"$f\")\n    h=$(sha \"$f\" || true)\n    ext=\"${f##*.}\"; ext=\"${ext,,}\"\n    case \"$ext\" in\n      zip) extra=$(list_zip \"$f\"); kind=\"zip\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"zip\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$extra\");;\n      tar|gz|tgz|bz2|xz) extra=$(list_tar \"$f\"); kind=\"tar\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"tar\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$extra\");;\n      db|sqlite|sqlite3) extra=$(list_sqlite \"$f\"); kind=\"sqlite\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"sqlite\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$extra\");;\n      sh|py|js|json|md|txt|cfg|ini|yml|yaml) preview=$(summ \"$f\" 12 | sed 's/[[:cntrl:]]//g'); kind=\"text\"; extra=\"preview\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"text\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"preview\":\"%s\"}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$preview\");;\n      *) kind=\"$(file -b --mime-type \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"?\")\"; extra=\"\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"%s\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\"}' \"$f\" \"$kind\" \"$size\" \"$h\");;\n    esac\n    printf '%s,%s,%s,\"%s\",\"%s\",\"%s\"\\n' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$kind\" \"${extra//\\\"/\\\"\\\"}\" \"${json//\\\"/\\\"\\\"}\" >> \"$CSV\"\n    printf '%s\\n' \"$json\" >> \"$JSON\"\n    sqlite3 \"$SQL\" \"INSERT OR REPLACE INTO files VALUES(?,?,?,?,?,?);\" \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$kind\" \"$extra\" \"$json\"\n  done < <(find -L \"$INBOX\" -type f -print0 2>/dev/null)\n  echo \"$(TS) [OK] CSV:$CSV JSONL:$JSON SQLITE:$SQL\" | tee -a \"$LOGI\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 backup (manifesto simbi\u00f3tico) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_backup(){\n  say \"[BK] empacotando\u2026\"\n  local stamp=\"$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)\"\n  local bundle=\"$BAK/state_$stamp.zip\"\n  local mtmp=\"$OUT/manifest_runtime.json\"\n  cat > \"$mtmp\" <<JSON\n{\n  \"run_at\":\"$(TS)\",\n  \"base\":\"$BASE\",\n  \"schema\":1,\n  \"paridade\":\"par\",\n  \"tesseract_hyperformas\":\"1 tesseract + 4 hyperformas\",\n  \"chave_simbiotica\":\"Fibonacci_mod + Voynich \ua66e-\u0394-\ud80c\udc80\"\n}\nJSON\n  ( cd \"$HOME\" && zip -qr \"$bundle\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$LOG\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$INDEX\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$OUT\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$mtmp\")\" \\\n  ) || true\n  say \"[BK] \u2192 $bundle\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 mirror (rclone) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_mirror(){\n  if ! command -v rclone >/dev/null 2>&1; then say \"[SYNC] rclone ausente; pulando\"; return 0; fi\n  local conf=\"$HOME/.config/rclone/rclone.conf\"\n  if grep -q 'PREENCHER' \"$conf\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    say \"[SYNC] rclone.conf com placeholder; configure com 'rclone config'\"; return 0\n  fi\n  local DST=\"VAULT:FCEA_OMEGA\"; local DATE=\"$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\"\n  say \"[SYNC] $BASE \u2192 $DST/$DATE\"\n  rclone copy \"$BASE\" \"$DST/$DATE\" --fast-list --checkers=6 --transfers=6 --tpslimit=8 --log-level INFO || true\n  say \"[SYNC] ok.\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 run (encadeado) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_run(){ say \"=== RUN in\u00edcio ===\"; sub_ingest; sub_index; sub_backup; sub_mirror; say \"=== RUN fim ===\"; }\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 help \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_help(){\n  cat <<H\nuso: $0 <fix-apt|init|tune|headsupd {start|stop|status}|ingest|index|backup|mirror|run|help>\n\nfix-apt     \u2014 normaliza APT (Signed-By \u00fanico; desabilita x11/root se falhar)\ninit        \u2014 deps, servi\u00e7os (crond), hardening leve\ntune        \u2014 Android 14 tuning (gera adb_once.sh e aplica root se houver)\nheadsupd    \u2014 daemon anti heads-up\ningest      \u2014 coleta (copy/link) p/ $INBOX  [INGEST_MODE=auto|copy|link, INGEST_CUTOFF_MB=50]\nindex       \u2014 indexa\u00e7\u00e3o profunda (CSV/JSONL/SQLite) em $INDEX (segue symlinks)\nbackup      \u2014 bundle com manifesto simbi\u00f3tico em $BAK\nmirror      \u2014 rclone \u2192 VAULT:FCEA_OMEGA (se rclone.conf v\u00e1lido)\nrun         \u2014 ingest \u2192 index \u2192 backup \u2192 mirror\nH\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 main \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\ncmd=\"${1:-help}\"\ncase \"$cmd\" in\n  fix-apt)   sub_fix_apt;;\n  init)      sub_init;;\n  tune)      sub_tune;;\n  headsupd)  shift; sub_headsupd \"${1:-status}\";;\n  ingest)    sub_ingest;;\n  index)     sub_index;;\n  backup)    sub_backup;;\n  mirror)    sub_mirror;;\n  run)       sub_run;;\n  help|*)    sub_help;;\nesac\nSH\nchmod +x ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh\n```\n\n### sequ\u00eancia sugerida agora\n```bash\n# 0) (opcional) liberar espa\u00e7o r\u00e1pido\nrm -f ~/FCEA_OMEGA/data/inbox/* 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# 1) APT limpo, sem conflitos\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh fix-apt\n\n# 2) Ambiente e servi\u00e7os\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh init\n\n# 3) Tuning A14 (gera adb_once.sh se sem root)\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh tune\n\n# 4) Heads-up (opcional)\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh headsupd start\n\n# 5) Pipeline (com ingest leve: s\u00f3 links se pouco espa\u00e7o)\nINGEST_MODE=auto INGEST_CUTOFF_MB=50 ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh run\n```\n\n#### Notas r\u00e1pidas, alinhadas com seus erros:\n- **Conflicting Signed-By**: agora removo **todas** as `.list` e reescrevo `.sources`. Se o `apt update` ainda chiar por root/x11, **eu mesmo desligo** esses reposit\u00f3rios e sigo.  \n- **\u201cUnable to locate package awk\u201d**: corrigido; fica `gawk`.  \n- **No space left on device**: ingest muda para **symlink** quando o espa\u00e7o < 512 MB (ou para arquivos > `INGEST_CUTOFF_MB`). O `index` usa `find -L`, ent\u00e3o segue os links sem duplicar bytes.  \n- **Log sem espa\u00e7o**: se o `/data` estiver < 200 MB, os logs v\u00e3o para **/sdcard/rafaelia_logs** automaticamente.\n\nSe quiser, eu plugo sua **assinatura simbi\u00f3tica** tamb\u00e9m nos nomes dos bundles de backup (ex.: `state_20250826_...__tesseract+4F_hkey-FibVoy.zip`) e como colunas extras no `index.sqlite`. Quer essa est\u00e9tica ritual\u00edstica tamb\u00e9m nos artefatos?"]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": true, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"finish_details": {"type": "stop", "stop_tokens": [200002]}, "is_complete": true, "citations": [], "content_references": [], "request_id": "97514a280bcd3652-FLN", "message_type": "variant", "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "requested_model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "8dc5913a-519b-45d1-9e9d-fce73c4f7796", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": "final"}, "parent": "8dc5913a-519b-45d1-9e9d-fce73c4f7796", "children": ["e5b5400a-2129-45c