"file-VD69HBciWd3eS5zn8y6gXG", "name": "d6e9db90fbd5ffb1158e68518e6f46005d1c78dbaef56427bb8a934c8f466c0a-2025-06-29-04-43-33-cefe5cb372804d79a18d0829d4655fee.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-E6ex7Q5RDm3xeQedoB7bbi", "name": "abra_leia_e via m\u00e1quina a maquina tem todas Minhas intera\u00e7\u00f5es entao eh para ler via bit a bit nem precisa descompactar pois eh bit a bit consegue sim.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-PsQS6wFk69ULTTtGPXZWzz", "name": "mapa.txt", "mimeType": "text/plain", "fileSizeTokens": 1153374}, {"id": "file-M3w1cXMmP62NAUVGDaVUoP", "name": "todos_scripts.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-Dn8VGcAD9Ea9zvdhAnU636", "name": "RAIO_X_RafaelIA.txt", "mimeType": "text/plain", "fileSizeTokens": 627926}, {"id": "file-VV4nFMtPnuhQU4gtqFc4MG", "name": "rafaelia_simbiotico.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}], "rebase_developer_message": true, "timestamp_": "absolute", "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "ba0ea5e6-1d8c-4380-be34-e1228c328a00", "children": ["bbb213fc-6197-44d5-8757-ee41b76755b9"]}, "51061091-e877-4fc5-9d63-c6abca5e8c10": {"id": "51061091-e877-4fc5-9d63-c6abca5e8c10", "message": {"id": "51061091-e877-4fc5-9d63-c6abca5e8c10", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189732.064621, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "thoughts", "thoughts": [{"summary": "Resolvendo problema de chave no APT", "content": "Vou sugerir um patch m\u00ednimo em portugu\u00eas para atualizar as se\u00e7\u00f5es do arquivo. Use os seguintes comandos no seu telefone para limpar duplicatas e chaves:\n\n1) Hotfix APT:\n   - rm *.list\n   - rm termux-main.gpg\n   - apt update\n\nAl\u00e9m disso, a chave ausente 1584981E6CDDB22D para x11/root deve ser corrigida ao assegurar que o arquivo .sources tenha \u201cSigned-By termux.gpg\u201d.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Fornecendo comandos de corre\u00e7\u00e3o", "content": "Primeiro, vamos limpar as listas e atualizar as chaves com:\n\n```\nrm -f $PREFIX/etc/apt/sources.list.d/*.list\nrm -f $PREFIX/etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/termux-main.gpg\npkg reinstall -y termux-keyring\napt-get clean && rm -rf $PREFIX/var/lib/apt/lists/*\napt update\n```\n\nDepois, para o pacote de inicializa\u00e7\u00e3o, substitua 'awk' por 'gawk' com um comando sed. Por fim, fornecerei um script emergencial para liberar espa\u00e7o no disco e aplicar melhorias rapidamente.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Atualizando o script para modifica\u00e7\u00e3o", "content": "Vamos criar uma nova vers\u00e3o com as modifica\u00e7\u00f5es propostas:\n\n- No \"fix-apt\", vamos deletar *.list e term", "chunks": [], "finished": true}], "source_analysis_msg_id": "2847c176-d38e-4e35-a517-904678daeefb"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "citations": [], "content_references": [], "classifier_response": "default", "skip_reasoning_title": "Pular", "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "9751452848b43652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "a21a0303-5d9c-420d-a223-3534cfafb1cd", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "a21a0303-5d9c-420d-a223-3534cfafb1cd", "children": ["a9bb0f61-7ae8-4074-a40a-a2feadaa7b50"]}, "bbb213fc-6197-44d5-8757-ee41b76755b9": {"id": "bbb213fc-6197-44d5-8757-ee41b76755b9", "message": {"id": "bbb213fc-6197-44d5-8757-ee41b76755b9", "author": {"role": "user", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756190283.314285, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["\n# 2) Ambiente e servi\u00e7os\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh init\n\n# 3) Tuning A14 (gera adb_once.sh se sem root)\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh tune\n\n# 4) Heads-up (opcional)\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh headsupd start\n\n# 5) Pipeline (com ingest leve: s\u00f3 links se pouco espa\u00e7o)\nINGEST_MODE=auto INGEST_CUTOFF_MB=50 ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh run\ndf: Unknown option 'm' (see \"df --help\")\ndf: Unknown option 'm' (see \"df --help\")\ndf: Unknown option 'm' (see \"df --help\")\ndf: Unknown option 'm' (see \"df --help\")\ndf: Unknown option 'm' (see \"df --help\")\n[\u221eFCEA] ~ $ # 0) (opcional) liberar espa\u00e7o r\u00e1pido\nrm -f ~/FCEA_OMEGA/data/inbox/* 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# 1) APT limpo, sem conflitos\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh fix-apt\n\n# 2) Ambiente e servi\u00e7os\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh init\n\n# 3) Tuning A14 (gera adb_once.sh se sem root)\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh tune\n\n# 4) Heads-up (opcional)\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh headsupd start\n\n# 5) Pipeline (com ingest leve: s\u00f3 links se pouco espa\u00e7o)\nINGEST_MODE=auto INGEST_CUTOFF_MB=50 ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh run\ndf: Unknown option 'm' (see \"df --help\")\ndf: Unknown option 'm' (see \"df --help\")\ndf: Unknown option 'm' (see \"df --help\")\ndf: Unknown option 'm' (see \"df --help\")\ndf: Unknown option 'm' (see \"df --help\")\n[\u221eFCEA] ~ $\n\n\n\nE modding no arquivo que eu enviei com as suas posi\u00e7\u00f5es para trabalhar direto no seu ambiente de forma ampla "]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"content_references": [], "search_result_groups": [], "search_queries": [], "image_results": [], "gizmo_id": "g-p-68abb00d154c81918b2161b6f4e99165", "real_time_audio_has_video": false, "dictation": false, "image_gen_async": false, "trigger_async_ux": false, "request_id": "975152eb0dc93652-FLN", "message_source": null, "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "e5b5400a-2129-45c5-b5e2-ce4a46a82f20", "children": ["bbb98e0b-286a-44e3-85a4-9c6c4c7166fd"]}, "a9bb0f61-7ae8-4074-a40a-a2feadaa7b50": {"id": "a9bb0f61-7ae8-4074-a40a-a2feadaa7b50", "message": {"id": "a9bb0f61-7ae8-4074-a40a-a2feadaa7b50", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189769.654314, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "reasoning_recap", "content": "Pensou por 42s"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "reasoning_ended", "finished_duration_sec": 42, "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "9751452848b43652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "51061091-e877-4fc5-9d63-c6abca5e8c10", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "51061091-e877-4fc5-9d63-c6abca5e8c10", "children": ["f2564e79-a34a-441d-8ba3-34c34c7d3007"]}, "bbb98e0b-286a-44e3-85a4-9c6c4c7166fd": {"id": "bbb98e0b-286a-44e3-85a4-9c6c4c7166fd", "message": {"id": "bbb98e0b-286a-44e3-85a4-9c6c4c7166fd", "author": {"role": "system", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756190292.8957207, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": [""]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": true, "weight": 0.0, "metadata": {"rebase_developer_message": true, "request_id": "975152eb0dc93652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "bbb213fc-6197-44d5-8757-ee41b76755b9", "timestamp_": "absolute", "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "bbb213fc-6197-44d5-8757-ee41b76755b9", "children": ["ed64c117-4802-41da-9b23-67c4c1b400e9"]}, "f2564e79-a34a-441d-8ba3-34c34c7d3007": {"id": "f2564e79-a34a-441d-8ba3-34c34c7d3007", "message": {"id": "f2564e79-a34a-441d-8ba3-34c34c7d3007", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756189726.575976, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["bora consertar tudo **no pr\u00f3prio telefone**, em 3 tiros certeiros:\n\n1) **Hotfix APT modded** (limpa duplicados `.list`, chave conflitante e refaz keyring).  \n2) **Limpeza de espa\u00e7o** imediata pra parar os \u201cNo space left on device\u201d.  \n3) **Script novo (`v7_mod2`)** j\u00e1 com:\n   - `fix-apt` que remove `.list` e o `termux-main.gpg` conflitando, e garante `Signed-By` \u00fanico.  \n   - `init` sem tentar instalar `awk` (o pacote correto \u00e9 `gawk`).  \n   - `ingest` com guardas de espa\u00e7o e **limite de tamanho** por arquivo (pula > 150 MB).  \n   - `headsupd` mais tolerante (espera o supervise aparecer).  \n   - index/backup/mirror idem ao anterior.\n\nFaz assim, colando os blocos abaixo **na ordem**:\n\n---\n\n## 1) Hotfix APT (roda j\u00e1)\n```bash\nPREFIX=/data/data/com.termux/files/usr\nAPT=\"$PREFIX/etc/apt\"\nSRC=\"$APT/sources.list.d\"\nTRUST=\"$APT/trusted.gpg.d\"\n\n# apaga listas antigas .list que est\u00e3o duplicando as fontes\nrm -f \"$SRC\"/*.list\n\n# remove a chave duplicada que causa \"Conflicting values ... termux-main.gpg\"\nrm -f \"$TRUST/termux-main.gpg\"\n\n# refor\u00e7a keyring\npkg reinstall -y termux-keyring || pkg install -y termux-keyring || true\n\n# reescreve .sources com Signed-By \u00fanico\ncat > \"$SRC/termux-main.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://packages.termux.dev/apt/termux-main\nSuites: stable\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\ncat > \"$SRC/x11.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://x11-packages.termux.net\nSuites: x11\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\ncat > \"$SRC/root.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://root-packages.termux.net\nSuites: root\nComponents: stable\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n\n# limpa caches e atualiza\napt-get clean\nrm -rf \"$APT/lists/\"* 2>/dev/null\napt update\n```\n\n> Isso remove os avisos \u201cConflicting values set for option Signed-By\u2026\u201d e os \u201cconfigured multiple times\u201d.\n\n---\n\n## 2) Liberar espa\u00e7o (r\u00e1pido)\n```bash\n# 2.1 \u2014 limpa inbox e caches grandes\nrm -rf ~/FCEA_OMEGA/data/inbox/* 2>/dev/null\napt-get clean\npkg clean\nrm -rf \"$PREFIX/tmp/\"* 2>/dev/null\n\n# 2.2 \u2014 mostra top 20 maiores no $HOME (pra decidir o que mover/apagar)\ndu -ah ~ 2>/dev/null | sort -hr | head -n 20\n\n# 2.3 \u2014 (opcional) cria uma pasta externa no SD e move bundles pesados pra l\u00e1\nmkdir -p /sdcard/FCEA_DROP\nmv ~/FCEA_OMEGA/backups/*.zip /sdcard/FCEA_DROP/ 2>/dev/null || true\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3) Script novo: `BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh`\nCole o bloco inteiro abaixo:\n\n```bash\ncat > ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh <<'SH'\n#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash\n# RAFAELIA \u2014 UNO v7_mod2 (fix APT + espa\u00e7o + ingest seguro + headsupd robusto)\n# subcmds: fix-apt | init | tune | headsupd {start|stop|status} | ingest | index | backup | mirror | run | help\nset -Eeuo pipefail\n\nTS(){ date '+%F %T'; }\nsay(){ printf '%s %s\\n' \"$(TS)\" \"$*\"; }\n\nPREFIX=\"/data/data/com.termux/files/usr\"\nAPT=\"$PREFIX/etc/apt\"\nSRC=\"$APT/sources.list.d\"\nTRUST=\"$APT/trusted.gpg.d\"\n\nBASE=\"${BASE:-$HOME/FCEA_OMEGA}\"\nETC=\"$BASE/etc\"; BIN=\"$BASE/bin\"; DATA=\"$BASE/data\"; OUT=\"$BASE/out\"; BAK=\"$BASE/backups\"\nINBOX=\"$DATA/inbox\"; INDEX=\"$BASE/index\"\nLOGDIR=\"$HOME/rafaelia_logs\"; mkdir -p \"$LOGDIR\" \"$ETC\" \"$BIN\" \"$DATA\" \"$OUT\" \"$BAK\" \"$INBOX\" \"$INDEX\"\nLOG=\"$LOGDIR/uno_v7_mod2.log\"; exec > >(tee -a \"$LOG\") 2>&1\nsay \"\u25b6 UNO v7_mod2 start\"\n\nneed(){ command -v \"$1\" >/dev/null 2>&1 || { say \"[MISS] $1\"; return 1; }; }\nfree_mb(){ df -Pm \"$HOME\" | awk 'NR==2{print $4}'; }\nsha(){ sha256sum \"$1\" 2>/dev/null | awk '{print $1}'; }\n\nFREE_MIN_MB=\"${FREE_MIN_MB:-600}\"   # se livre < 600 MB, n\u00e3o copia nada pro INBOX\nMAX_COPY_MB=\"${MAX_COPY_MB:-150}\"   # n\u00e3o copia arquivos maiores que 150 MB\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500 fix-apt: elimina duplicados .list e chave conflitante\nsub_fix_apt(){\n  say \"[APT] normalizando reposit\u00f3rios\u2026\"\n  rm -f \"$SRC\"/*.list\n  rm -f \"$TRUST/termux-main.gpg\"\n  pkg reinstall -y termux-keyring || pkg install -y termux-keyring || true\n  apt-get clean || true\n  rm -rf \"$APT/lists/\"* 2>/dev/null || true\n  cat > \"$SRC/termux-main.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://packages.termux.dev/apt/termux-main\nSuites: stable\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n  cat > \"$SRC/x11.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://x11-packages.termux.net\nSuites: x11\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n  cat > \"$SRC/root.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://root-packages.termux.net\nSuites: root\nComponents: stable\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n  apt update\n  say \"[APT] ok.\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500 init: deps corretos (usa gawk; N\u00c3O tenta 'awk') + servi\u00e7os\nsub_init(){\n  say \"[INIT] deps + servi\u00e7os\u2026\"\n  pkg install -y termux-services || true\n  mkdir -p \"$PREFIX/var/service\" || true\n  sv-enable crond 2>/dev/null || true\n  sv up crond 2>/dev/null || true\n\n  pkg install -y coreutils findutils tar gzip xz-utils zip unzip p7zip \\\n                 gawk sed grep ripgrep sqlite sox ffmpeg util-linux \\\n                 python nodejs-lts file || true\n\n  command -v termux-setup-storage >/dev/null 2>&1 && termux-setup-storage || true\n  grep -q 'umask 077' \"$HOME/.bashrc\" 2>/dev/null || echo 'umask 077'>>\"$HOME/.bashrc\"\n  chmod -R go-rwx \"$BASE\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  say \"[INIT] ok. BASE=$BASE\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500 tune: Android 14 (gera adb_once.sh; aplica root se houver)\nsub_tune(){\n  say \"[TUNE] Android 14\u2026\"\n  sub_init\n  local is_root=0\n  if command -v su >/dev/null 2>&1 && su -c id | grep -q \"uid=0\"; then is_root=1; fi\n\n  local ADB=\"$HOME/adb_once.sh\"\n  cat > \"$ADB\" <<'ADB'\n#!/system/bin/sh\ncmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux\ncmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux.api 2>/dev/null || true\nappops set com.termux RUN_ANY_IN_BACKGROUND allow 2>/dev/null || true\nappops set com.termux WAKE_LOCK allow 2>/dev/null || true\nsettings put global app_standby_enabled 0 2>/dev/null || true\nsettings put global heads_up_notifications_enabled 0 2>/dev/null || true\nADB\n  chmod +x \"$ADB\"\n  say \"[TUNE] gerado $ADB (use via ADB se sem root).\"\n\n  if [ \"$is_root\" -eq 1 ]; then\n    su -c \"cmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux\" || true\n    su -c \"cmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux.api\" || true\n    su -c \"appops set com.termux RUN_ANY_IN_BACKGROUND allow\" || true\n    su -c \"appops set com.termux WAKE_LOCK allow\" || true\n    su -c \"settings put global heads_up_notifications_enabled 0\" || true\n    su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 1\" || true; sleep 0.2; su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 0\" || true\n    say \"[TUNE] ajustes root aplicados.\"\n  fi\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500 heads-up cleaner: espera supervise aparecer\nsub_headsupd(){\n  local action=\"${1:-status}\"\n  local SVC=\"$PREFIX/var/service/heads-up-cleaner\"\n  case \"$action\" in\n    start)\n      mkdir -p \"$SVC\"\n      cat > \"$SVC/run\" <<'R'\n#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash\nset -Eeuo pipefail\nLOG=\"$HOME/rafaelia_logs/heads_up_cleaner.log\"; mkdir -p \"${LOG%/*}\"\nis_root(){ command -v su >/dev/null 2>&1 && su -c id | grep -q 'uid=0'; }\n# aguarda runit inicializar supervise\nfor i in $(seq 1 20); do [ -e supervise/ok ] && break || sleep 0.2; done\nif ! is_root; then\n  echo \"$(date '+%F %T') [WARN] sem root: efeito limitado\" >> \"$LOG\"\n  while :; do sleep 30; done\nfi\nwhile :; do\n  su -c \"cmd statusbar collapse-panels\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 1\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 0.2\n  su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 0\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 3\ndone\nR\n      chmod +x \"$SVC/run\"\n      sv up heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true\n      # brev\u00edssima espera e checagem\n      sleep 1\n      sv status heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true\n      say \"[HUN] daemon iniciado.\"\n      ;;\n    stop)   sv down heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true; sv-disable heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true; say \"[HUN] parado.\";;\n    status) sv status heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || { say \"[HUN] servi\u00e7o ausente\"; } ;;\n    *)      say \"uso: $0 headsupd {start|stop|status}\";;\n  esac\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500 ingest: respeita espa\u00e7o e limita tamanho de c\u00f3pia\nsub_ingest(){\n  say \"[INGEST] varrendo fontes\u2026\"\n  local globs=\"${SCAN_GLOBS:-/sdcard/Download/* /sdcard/*}\"\n  local count=0 dest f\n  mkdir -p \"$INBOX\"\n\n  local free=\"$(free_mb)\"\n  if [ \"${free:-0}\" -lt \"$FREE_MIN_MB\" ]; then\n    say \"[INGEST] espa\u00e7o livre ${free}MB < ${FREE_MIN_MB}MB \u2192 N\u00c3O copiar; rode index direto depois.\"\n    return 0\n  fi\n\n  shopt -s nullglob dotglob\n  for pattern in $globs; do\n    if [ -d \"$pattern\" ]; then\n      while IFS= read -r -d '' f; do\n        [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n        # pula grandes\n        sz=$(stat -c %s \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || stat -f %z \"$f\")\n        if [ \"$sz\" -gt $((MAX_COPY_MB*1024*1024)) ]; then\n          say \"[INGEST] skip >${MAX_COPY_MB}MB: $(basename \"$f\")\"\n          continue\n        fi\n        dest=\"$INBOX/$(basename \"$f\")\"\n        if [ ! -e \"$dest\" ]; then cp -n -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true; fi\n      done < <(find \"$pattern\" -maxdepth 1 -type f -print0 2>/dev/null)\n    else\n      for f in $pattern; do\n        [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n        sz=$(stat -c %s \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || stat -f %z \"$f\")\n        if [ \"$sz\" -gt $((MAX_COPY_MB*1024*1024)) ]; then\n          say \"[INGEST] skip >${MAX_COPY_MB}MB: $(basename \"$f\")\"\n          continue\n        fi\n        dest=\"$INBOX/$(basename \"$f\")\"\n        if [ ! -e \"$dest\" ]; then cp -n -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true; fi\n      done\n    fi\n  done\n  shopt -u nullglob dotglob\n  say \"[INGEST] $count novos \u2192 $INBOX\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500 index: mesma de antes\nsub_index(){\n  say \"[INDEX] cat\u00e1logo profundo\u2026\"\n  local free=\"$(free_mb)\"; [ \"${free:-0}\" -lt 200 ] && { say \"[INDEX] abort: livre ${free}MB < 200MB\"; return 0; }\n  local CSV=\"$INDEX/index.csv\"; local JSON=\"$INDEX/index.jsonl\"; local SQL=\"$INDEX/index.sqlite\"; local LOGI=\"$INDEX/index.log\"\n  mkdir -p \"$INDEX\"; : > \"$JSON\"; : > \"$CSV\"; echo 'path,size_bytes,sha256,kind,extra,json' > \"$CSV\"\n  need sqlite3 || pkg install -y sqlite || true\n  sqlite3 \"$SQL\" 'PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL; CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS files(path TEXT PRIMARY KEY,size_bytes INTEGER,sha256 TEXT,kind TEXT,extra TEXT,json TEXT);'\n\n  list_zip(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport zipfile,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  with zipfile.ZipFile(p,'r') as z:\n    infos=[{'name':i.filename,'size':i.file_size,'comp':i.compress_size} for i in z.infolist() if not i.is_dir()]\n    print(json.dumps({'entries':len(infos),'top':infos[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  list_tar(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport tarfile,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  with tarfile.open(p,'r:*') as t:\n    names=[m.name for m in t.getmembers() if m.isfile()]\n    print(json.dumps({'entries':len(names),'top':names[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  list_sqlite(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport sqlite3,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  con=sqlite3.connect(p); cur=con.cursor()\n  cur.execute(\"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table'\"); tabs=[r[0] for r in cur.fetchall()]\n  info={}\n  for t in tabs[:25]:\n    try: cur.execute(f\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM '{t}'\"); info[t]=cur.fetchone()[0]\n    except Exception as e: info[t]=str(e)\n  print(json.dumps({'tables':len(tabs),'counts':info,'sample':tabs[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  summ(){ head -n \"${2:-12}\" \"$1\" 2>/dev/null | tr -d '\\r' | sed 's/\"/'\\''/g'; }\n\n  echo \"$(TS) [START] $INBOX \u2192 $INDEX\" | tee -a \"$LOGI\"\n  while IFS= read -r -d '' f; do\n    size=$(stat -c %s \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || stat -f %z \"$f\")\n    h=$(sha \"$f\" || true)\n    ext=\"${f##*.}\"; ext=\"${ext,,}\"\n    case \"$ext\" in\n      zip) extra=$(list_zip \"$f\"); kind=\"zip\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"zip\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$extra\");;\n      tar|gz|tgz|bz2|xz) extra=$(list_tar \"$f\"); kind=\"tar\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"tar\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$extra\");;\n      db|sqlite|sqlite3) extra=$(list_sqlite \"$f\"); kind=\"sqlite\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"sqlite\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$extra\");;\n      sh|py|js|json|md|txt|cfg|ini|yml|yaml) preview=$(summ \"$f\" 12 | sed 's/[[:cntrl:]]//g'); kind=\"text\"; extra=\"preview\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"text\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"preview\":\"%s\"}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$preview\");;\n      *) kind=\"$(file -b --mime-type \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"?\")\"; extra=\"\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"%s\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\"}' \"$f\" \"$kind\" \"$size\" \"$h\");;\n    esac\n    printf '%s,%s,%s,\"%s\",\"%s\",\"%s\"\\n' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$kind\" \"${extra//\\\"/\\\"\\\"}\" \"${json//\\\"/\\\"\\\"}\" >> \"$CSV\"\n    printf '%s\\n' \"$json\" >> \"$JSON\"\n    sqlite3 \"$SQL\" \"INSERT OR REPLACE INTO files VALUES(?,?,?,?,?,?);\" \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$kind\" \"$extra\" \"$json\"\n  done < <(find \"$INBOX\" -type f -print0 2>/dev/null)\n  echo \"$(TS) [OK] CSV:$CSV JSONL:$JSON SQLITE:$SQL\" | tee -a \"$LOGI\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500 backup: manifesto simbi\u00f3tico\nsub_backup(){\n  say \"[BK] empacotando\u2026\"\n  local stamp=\"$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)\"\n  local bundle=\"$BAK/state_$stamp.zip\"\n  local mtmp=\"$OUT/manifest_runtime.json\"\n  cat > \"$mtmp\" <<JSON\n{\n  \"run_at\":\"$(TS)\",\n  \"base\":\"$BASE\",\n  \"schema\":1,\n  \"paridade\":\"par\",\n  \"tesseract_hyperformas\":\"1 tesseract + 4 hyperformas\",\n  \"chave_simbiotica\":\"Fibonacci_mod + Voynich \ua66e-\u0394-\ud80c\udc80\"\n}\nJSON\n  ( cd \"$HOME\" && zip -qr \"$bundle\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$LOG\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$INDEX\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$OUT\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$mtmp\")\" \\\n  ) || true\n  say \"[BK] \u2192 $bundle\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500 mirror: rclone\nsub_mirror(){\n  if ! command -v rclone >/dev/null 2>&1; then say \"[SYNC] rclone ausente; pulando\"; return 0; fi\n  local conf=\"$HOME/.config/rclone/rclone.conf\"\n  if grep -q 'PREENCHER' \"$conf\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    say \"[SYNC] rclone.conf com placeholder; configure com 'rclone config'\"; return 0\n  fi\n  local DST=\"VAULT:FCEA_OMEGA\"; local DATE=\"$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\"\n  say \"[SYNC] $BASE \u2192 $DST/$DATE\"\n  rclone copy \"$BASE\" \"$DST/$DATE\" --fast-list --checkers=6 --transfers=6 --tpslimit=8 --log-level INFO || true\n  say \"[SYNC] ok.\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500 run encadeado\nsub_run(){ say \"=== RUN in\u00edcio ===\"; sub_ingest; sub_index; sub_backup; sub_mirror; say \"=== RUN fim ===\"; }\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500 help\nsub_help(){\n  cat <<H\nuso: $0 <fix-apt|init|tune|headsupd {start|stop|status}|ingest|index|backup|mirror|run|help>\n\nfix-apt     \u2014 normaliza APT (Signed-By \u00fanico; remove .list e chave duplicada)\ninit        \u2014 deps, servi\u00e7os (crond), hardening leve\ntune        \u2014 Android 14 tuning (gera adb_once.sh; aplica root se houver)\nheadsupd    \u2014 daemon anti heads-up (tolerante a supervise)\ningest      \u2014 coleta \u2192 INBOX (respeita FREE_MIN_MB e MAX_COPY_MB)\nindex       \u2014 indexa\u00e7\u00e3o profunda (CSV/JSONL/SQLite) em $INDEX\nbackup      \u2014 bundle com manifesto simbi\u00f3tico em $BAK\nmirror      \u2014 rclone \u2192 VAULT:FCEA_OMEGA (se rclone.conf v\u00e1lido)\nrun         \u2014 ingest \u2192 index \u2192 backup \u2192 mirror\nvars        \u2014 FREE_MIN_MB=${FREE_MIN_MB}  MAX_COPY_MB=${MAX_COPY_MB}\nH\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500 main\ncmd=\"${1:-help}\"\ncase \"$cmd\" in\n  fix-apt)   sub_fix_apt;;\n  init)      sub_init;;\n  tune)      sub_tune;;\n  headsupd)  shift; sub_headsupd \"${1:-status}\";;\n  ingest)    sub_ingest;;\n  index)     sub_index;;\n  backup)    sub_backup;;\n  mirror)    sub_mirror;;\n  run)       sub_run;;\n  help|*)    sub_help;;\nesac\nSH\nchmod +x ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4) Rodar a sequ\u00eancia (com limites ativados)\n```bash\n# j\u00e1 aplicou o Hotfix APT e limpou espa\u00e7o no passo 1 e 2\n\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh fix-apt\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh init\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh tune\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh headsupd start\n\n# voc\u00ea pode ajustar os limites assim:\nFREE_MIN_MB=800 MAX_COPY_MB=120 ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh run\n```\n\nSe ainda aparecer \u201cNo space left on device\u201d durante **ingest**, \u00e9 porque o armazenamento **caiu abaixo de `FREE_MIN_MB` ap\u00f3s algumas c\u00f3pias**. Nesse caso, suba o limite (ex.: `FREE_MIN_MB=1200`) ou rode em duas fases:\n\n```bash\nFREE_MIN_MB=1200 ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh ingest   # provavelmente pular\u00e1 tudo (ok)\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh index                      # indexa s\u00f3 o que j\u00e1 estiver no INBOX\n```\n\nQuer a pr\u00f3xima camada? Posso te dar um `index_direct` que **indexa direto do /sdcard** sem copiar nada (s\u00f3 leitura), ideal pra quando o espa\u00e7o interno estiver no osso."]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": true, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"citations": [], "content_references": [], "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "9751452848b43652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "a9bb0f61-7ae8-4074-a40a-a2feadaa7b50", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": "final"}, "parent": "a9bb0f61-7ae8-4074-a40a-a2feadaa7b50", "children": []}, "ed64c117-4802-41da-9b23-67c4c1b400e9": {"id": "ed64c117-4802-41da-9b23-67c4c1b400e9", "message": {"id": "ed64c117-4802-41da-9b23-67c4c1b400e9", "author": {"role": "system", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756190293.0424757, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": [""]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"is_contextual_answers_system_message": true, "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true, "command": "prompt", "contextual_answers_message_type": "sources_and_filters_prompt", "request_id": "975152eb0dc93652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "bbb98e0b-286a-44e3-85a4-9c6c4c7166fd", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "bbb98e0b-286a-44e3-85a4-9c6c4c7166fd", "children": ["fcdec6c0-3d51-4c3f-a918-a066113d0256"]}, "fcdec6c0-3d51-4c3f-a918-a066113d0256": {"id": "fcdec6c0-3d51-4c3f-a918-a066113d0256", "message": {"id": "fcdec6c0-3d51-4c3f-a918-a066113d0256", "author": {"role": "tool", "name": "file_search", "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756190293.1414359, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "tether_browsing_display", "result": "", "summary": "", "assets": null, "tether_id": null}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 0.0, "metadata": {"command": "spinner", "status": "running", "reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true, "classifier_response": "default", "request_id": "975152eb0dc93652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "ed64c117-4802-41da-9b23-67c4c1b400e9", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "ed64c117-4802-41da-9b23-67c4c1b400e9", "childr