ion": true, "command": "prompt", "contextual_answers_message_type": "sources_and_filters_prompt", "request_id": "975162e7d9ca3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "7c9b9b95-d761-444c-98a4-74a56c5deffa", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "7c9b9b95-d761-444c-98a4-74a56c5deffa", "children": ["da96eac2-1900-4740-946b-3be607d20ab8"]}, "da96eac2-1900-4740-946b-3be607d20ab8": {"id": "da96eac2-1900-4740-946b-3be607d20ab8", "message": {"id": "da96eac2-1900-4740-946b-3be607d20ab8", "author": {"role": "tool", "name": "file_search", "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756190965.541981, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "tether_browsing_display", "result": "", "summary": "", "assets": null, "tether_id": null}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 0.0, "metadata": {"command": "spinner", "status": "running", "reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true, "classifier_response": "default", "request_id": "975162e7d9ca3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "f75e0348-3439-454f-b8ae-2617fdf1d472", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "f75e0348-3439-454f-b8ae-2617fdf1d472", "children": ["e96dc97a-1ec7-43a0-939f-dcdd68f46ab7"]}, "e96dc97a-1ec7-43a0-939f-dcdd68f46ab7": {"id": "e96dc97a-1ec7-43a0-939f-dcdd68f46ab7", "message": {"id": "e96dc97a-1ec7-43a0-939f-dcdd68f46ab7", "author": {"role": "tool", "name": "file_search", "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756190966.0502183, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["The files uploaded by the user in the current message have been fully loaded. Searching won't provide additional information from these specific files. However, remember that some of the previously uploaded files were not fully loaded, so you should invoke msearch to search their full content as needed."]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true, "reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "classifier_response": "default", "request_id": "975162e7d9ca3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "da96eac2-1900-4740-946b-3be607d20ab8", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "da96eac2-1900-4740-946b-3be607d20ab8", "children": ["5ece5bba-8b23-4310-93c1-0bd899b68fb2"]}, "5ece5bba-8b23-4310-93c1-0bd899b68fb2": {"id": "5ece5bba-8b23-4310-93c1-0bd899b68fb2", "message": {"id": "5ece5bba-8b23-4310-93c1-0bd899b68fb2", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756190966.299998, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "thoughts", "thoughts": [{"summary": "Analisando o erro do SQLite", "content": "O usu\u00e1rio apresenta um erro do SQLite: \"in prepare, near '/': syntax error\". Parece que est\u00e1 lidando com um caminho que inclui um arquivo oculto que come\u00e7a com \".trashed-\". O comando SQL \"INSERT OR REPLACE INTO files\" parece correto, mas talvez o problema esteja no caminho, que conta com caracteres especiais como \"-\". Isso pode estar sendo interpretado de maneira errada.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Investigando erro no sqlite3", "content": "Parece que o severo erro pode ocorrer porque o sqlite3 interpreta o caminho do arquivo come\u00e7ando com \"/\" como um comando separado. Eu tamb\u00e9m passei o comando PRAGMA antes da cria\u00e7\u00e3o da tabela, e isso acabou sendo aceito. Imagino que o erro pode estar relacionado ao tratamento de newline ou NULL nos arquivos. Algu\u00e9m deve conferir o par\u00e2metro de comando.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Analisando erro do SQLite", "content": "O comando sqlite3 realmente n\u00e3o suporta par\u00e2metros com \"?\" diretamente da linha de comando. No entanto, \u00e9 poss\u00edvel usar os valores diretamente, como \"insert into t values(?,?,?)\" com os valores na sequ\u00eancia, que est\u00e1 correto. Mas o erro sugere que o SQL foi interpretado como caminho, possivelmente devido a novos caracteres ou uma vari\u00e1vel vazia. Eu tamb\u00e9m duvido que o problema seja o nome da tabela, \"files\".", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Investigando problema no SQLite", "content": "Estou pensando que o erro pode estar relacionado ao uso de caracteres `%` ou ao tamanho do valor de `$json`, que pode estar grande demais ou incluir quebras de linha, o que pode causar problemas no binding de par\u00e2metros no sqlite3 CLI. Outra op\u00e7\u00e3o seria usar `.import --csv` para evitar problemas com o CLI.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}], "source_analysis_msg_id": "91603094-d510-4724-870f-80c114c50bea"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "citations": [], "content_references": [], "classifier_response": "default", "skip_reasoning_title": "Pular", "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "975162e7d9ca3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "e96dc97a-1ec7-43a0-939f-dcdd68f46ab7", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "e96dc97a-1ec7-43a0-939f-dcdd68f46ab7", "children": ["be66e901-ed33-4a6e-b02f-097356781a60"]}, "be66e901-ed33-4a6e-b02f-097356781a60": {"id": "be66e901-ed33-4a6e-b02f-097356781a60", "message": {"id": "be66e901-ed33-4a6e-b02f-097356781a60", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191011.225905, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "reasoning_recap", "content": "Pensou por 45s"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "reasoning_ended", "finished_duration_sec": 45, "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "975162e7d9ca3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "5ece5bba-8b23-4310-93c1-0bd899b68fb2", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "5ece5bba-8b23-4310-93c1-0bd899b68fb2", "children": ["8306a4c3-498e-4162-89f9-a9ec4689c16e"]}, "8306a4c3-498e-4162-89f9-a9ec4689c16e": {"id": "8306a4c3-498e-4162-89f9-a9ec4689c16e", "message": {"id": "8306a4c3-498e-4162-89f9-a9ec4689c16e", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756190954.635944, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["boa! o `mod3` andou, mas teu log mostrou um pepino no **INSERT do SQLite**:\n\n```\nError: in prepare, near \"/\": syntax error\n  /data/.../inbox/.trashed-...   \u2190 o sqlite tentou \u201cexecutar\u201d o caminho como SQL\n```\n\nIsso acontece quando a CLI do `sqlite3` perde a string SQL e fica s\u00f3 com os \u201cpar\u00e2metros\u201d (o caminho come\u00e7ando por `/`). Pode rolar com certos nomes \u201cesquisitos\u201d (ex.: `.trashed-*`) + volumes grandes de argumentos. Vambora blindar:\n\n## Hotfix r\u00e1pido (in-place) pro `v7_mod3`\n1) **Pula** arquivos ocultos \u201clixo\u201d (`.trashed-*`, `.Trash*`).  \n2) Troca o `INSERT` via CLI por **INSERT via Python** (robusto com qualquer nome/JSON).\n\nCole e rode:\n\n```bash\ncat > ~/hotfix_sqlite_insert.sh <<'SH'\n#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash\nset -Eeuo pipefail\nF=~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod3.sh\n[ -f \"$F\" ] || { echo \"arquivo n\u00e3o encontrado: $F\"; exit 1; }\n\n# 1) adicionar helper py_insert() uma \u00fanica vez (antes de sub_index)\nawk '\n/^sub_index\\(\\)\\{/ && !ins{\n  print \"py_insert(){\"\n  print \"  python - \\\"$1\\\" <<\\\"PY\\\"\"\n  print \"import sys,sqlite3,json\"\n  print \"db=sys.argv[1]\"\n  print \"rec=json.loads(sys.stdin.read())\"\n  print \"con=sqlite3.connect(db)\"\n  print \"con.execute(\\\"PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL;\\\")\"\n  print \"con.execute(\\\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS files(path TEXT PRIMARY KEY,size_bytes INTEGER,sha256 TEXT,kind TEXT,extra TEXT,json TEXT);\\\")\"\n  print \"con.execute(\\\"INSERT OR REPLACE INTO files VALUES(?,?,?,?,?,?)\\\",(\"\n  print \"  rec[\\\"path\\\"], int(rec[\\\"size\\\"]), rec.get(\\\"sha256\\\",\\\"\\\"), rec.get(\\\"kind\\\",\\\"\\\"), rec.get(\\\"extra\\\",\\\"\\\"), json.dumps(rec,ensure_ascii=False)\"\n  print \"))\"\n  print \"con.commit(); con.close()\"\n  print \"PY\"\n  print \"}\"\n  print \"\"; ins=1\n}\n{ print }\n' \"$F\" > \"$F.tmp\" && mv \"$F.tmp\" \"$F\"\n\n# 2) patch dentro de sub_index:\n#   - pula basenames que comecem com . ou .trashed-\n#   - monta o JSON final e chama py_insert em vez de sqlite3 CLI\nawk '\nBEGIN{in=0}\n/^sub_index\\(\\)\\{/ { in=1; print; next }\nin && /echo \"\\$\\(\\TS\\) \\[START\\]/ { print; next }\nin && /while IFS= read -r -d .. f; do/ { print; print \"    base=$(basename \\\"$f\\\")\"; print \"    [[ \\\"$base\\\" = .* ]] && continue\"; print \"    [[ \\\"$base\\\" = .trashed-* ]] && continue\"; next }\nin && /sqlite3 \"\\$SQL\" \"INSERT OR REPLACE INTO files/ {\n  print \"    rec_json=\\\"$json\\\"\"\n  print \"    py_insert \\\"$SQL\\\" <<< \\\"$rec_json\\\"\"\n  print \"    continue\"\n  next\n}\nin && /printf .* >> \"\\$CSV\"/ {\n  # tamb\u00e9m injeta campo extra no JSON que j\u00e1 existe\n  # reconstru\u00edmos json com campo \\\"extra\\\" quando for text/zip/tar/sqlite\n  gsub(/printf .*/, \"    : # CSV write mantido abaixo\", $0); print; next\n}\nin && /^\\s*printf .* >> \"\\$JSON\"/ { print; next }\nin && /^\\s*done < <\\(find -L/ { print; next }\n{ print }\n' \"$F\" > \"$F.tmp\" && mv \"$F.tmp\" \"$F\"\n\n# 3) Garantir que continuamos salvando CSV/JSON\n# (se o bloco acima tiver removido, reescreve as duas linhas imediatamente antes do py_insert)\nawk '\nBEGIN{in=0}\n/^sub_index\\(\\)\\{/ { in=1 }\nin && /rec_json=\"\\$json\"/ {\n  print \"    printf '\\''%s,%s,%s,\\\"%s\\\",\\\"%s\\\",\\\"%s\\\"\\\\n'\\'' \\\"$f\\\" \\\"$size\\\" \\\"$h\\\" \\\"$kind\\\" \\\"${extra//\\\"\\\"/\\\"\\\"}\\\" \\\"${json//\\\"\\\"/\\\"\\\"}\\\" >> \\\"$CSV\\\"\"\n  print \"    printf '\\''%s\\\\n'\\'' \\\"$json\\\" >> \\\"$JSON\\\"\"\n}\n{ print }\n' \"$F\" > \"$F.tmp\" && mv \"$F.tmp\" \"$F\"\n\necho \"[ok] hotfix aplicado em $F\"\nSH\nchmod +x ~/hotfix_sqlite_insert.sh\n~/hotfix_sqlite_insert.sh\n```\n\n## Rodar de novo (com skip de lixo e insert robusto)\n```bash\n# s\u00f3 recome\u00e7ar o passo run; o resto j\u00e1 est\u00e1 ok\nINGEST_MODE=auto INGEST_CUTOFF_MB=50 ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod3.sh run\n```\n\n### Por que isso resolve?\n- **`.trashed-*`** e afins ficam de fora \u2014 menos barulho.\n- O **`sqlite3` via Python** n\u00e3o sofre com nomes/path malucos, que \u00e0s vezes bagun\u00e7am o parsing da CLI do sqlite.\n- Voc\u00ea continua ganhando CSV + JSONL + SQLite, s\u00f3 que \u00e0 prova de tudo.\n\nSe preferir, eu tamb\u00e9m aplico esse mesmo patch dentro do **seu script \u201ccan\u00f4nico\u201d** (aquele que voc\u00ea j\u00e1 usa no dia a dia). Diz qual \u00e9 o caminho dele que eu te devolvo o patch pronto no mesmo estilo \u201ccolar com `cat`\u201d."]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": true, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"citations": [], "content_references": [], "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "975162e7d9ca3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "be66e901-ed33-4a6e-b02f-097356781a60", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": "final"}, "parent": "be66e901-ed33-4a6e-b02f-097356781a60", "children": ["4ee0f034-c38a-4171-bf3f-f7053dd283ab"]}, "4ee0f034-c38a-4171-bf3f-f7053dd283ab": {"id": "4ee0f034-c38a-4171-bf3f-f7053dd283ab", "message": {"id": "4ee0f034-c38a-4171-bf3f-f7053dd283ab", "author": {"role": "system", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191155.1493344, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": [""]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"attachments": [{"id": "file-Fzi28rdbSfR3GVc8yeJFFt", "name": "JSON.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-1LhzSbDKvtcemqcxggHNY7", "name": "backup_20250528_005117.tar.gz", "mimeType": "application/gzip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-8n7eB6f8H7D7x96W7nSxW7", "name": "29ccc67a-7890-11f0-8b77-e00e72c952c1.tar.gz", "mimeType": "application/gzip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-VD69HBciWd3eS5zn8y6gXG", "name": "d6e9db90fbd5ffb1158e68518e6f46005d1c78dbaef56427bb8a934c8f466c0a-2025-06-29-04-43-33-cefe5cb372804d79a18d0829d4655fee.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-E6ex7Q5RDm3xeQedoB7bbi", "name": "abra_leia_e via m\u00e1quina a maquina tem todas Minhas intera\u00e7\u00f5es entao eh para ler via bit a bit nem precisa descompactar pois eh bit a bit consegue sim.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-PsQS6wFk69ULTTtGPXZWzz", "name": "mapa.txt", "mimeType": "text/plain", "fileSizeTokens": 1153374}, {"id": "file-M3w1cXMmP62NAUVGDaVUoP", "name": "todos_scripts.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-Dn8VGcAD9Ea9zvdhAnU636", "name": "RAIO_X_RafaelIA.txt", "mimeType": "text/plain", "fileSizeTokens": 627926}, {"id": "file-VV4nFMtPnuhQU4gtqFc4MG", "name": "rafaelia_simbiotico.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}], "rebase_developer_message": true, "timestamp_": "absolute", "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "8306a4c3-498e-4162-89f9-a9ec4689c16e", "children": ["bbb216d8-c199-4f4c-9891-b33a697e53ee"]}, "bbb216d8-c199-4f4c-9891-b33a697e53ee": {"id": "bbb216d8-c199-4f4c-9891-b33a697e53ee", "message": {"id": "bbb216d8-c199-4f4c-9891-b33a697e53ee", "author": {"role": "user", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191155.310339, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["\n\necho \"[ok] hotfix aplicado em $F\"\nSH\nchmod +x ~/hotfix_sqlite_insert.sh                                                        ~/hotfix_sqlite_insert.sh\nawk: cmd. line:2: BEGIN{in=0}\nawk: cmd. line:2:       ^ syntax error\nawk: cmd. line:2: BEGIN{in=0}\nawk: cmd. line:2:       ^ syntax error\n[ok] hotfix aplicado em /data/data/com.termux/files/home/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod3.sh\n[\u221eFCEA] ~ $ # s\u00f3 recome\u00e7ar o passo run; o resto j\u00e1 est\u00e1 ok\nINGEST_MODE=auto INGEST_CUTOFF_MB=50 ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod3.sh run\nbash: /data/data/com.termux/files/home/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod3.sh: Permission denied\n[\u221eFCEA] ~ $"]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"content_references": [], "search_result_groups": [], "search_queries": [], "image_results": [], "gizmo_id": "g-p-68abb00d154c81918b2161b6f4e99165", "real_time_audio_has_video": false, "dictation": false, "image_gen_async": false, "trigger_async_ux": false, "request_id": "97516821caab3652-FLN", "message_source": null, "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "4ee0f034-c38a-4171-bf3f-f7053dd283ab", "children": ["dde7b642-eebb-4d44-a171-b1efa4a9de91"]}, "dde7b642-eebb-4d44-a171-b1efa4a9de91": {"id": "dde7b642-eebb-4d44-a171-b1efa4a9de91", "message": {"id": "dde7b642-eebb-4d44-a171-b1efa4a9de91", "author": {"role": "system", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191171.0976143, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": [""]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": true, "weight": 0.0, "metadata": {"rebase_developer_message": true, "request_id": "97516821caab3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "bbb216d8-c199-4f4c-9891-b33a697e53ee", "timestamp_": "absolute", "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "bbb216d8-c199-4f4c-9891-b33a697e53ee", "children": ["43691c4d-8759-494c-ac3a-69185