 "660ecd99-e4f8-44d1-8529-3469aa5f12f8", "author": {"role": "system", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191173.0760643, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": [""]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"is_contextual_answers_system_message": true, "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true, "command": "prompt", "contextual_answers_message_type": "sources_and_filters_prompt", "request_id": "97516821caab3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "9199f7ba-ab56-4fb0-b2d2-3c1507a1b8c9", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "9199f7ba-ab56-4fb0-b2d2-3c1507a1b8c9", "children": ["6e21d8f5-a5c6-4570-bd82-73458609861c"]}, "6e21d8f5-a5c6-4570-bd82-73458609861c": {"id": "6e21d8f5-a5c6-4570-bd82-73458609861c", "message": {"id": "6e21d8f5-a5c6-4570-bd82-73458609861c", "author": {"role": "tool", "name": "file_search", "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191174.1880095, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "tether_browsing_display", "result": "", "summary": "", "assets": null, "tether_id": null}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 0.0, "metadata": {"command": "spinner", "status": "running", "reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true, "classifier_response": "default", "request_id": "97516821caab3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "660ecd99-e4f8-44d1-8529-3469aa5f12f8", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "660ecd99-e4f8-44d1-8529-3469aa5f12f8", "children": ["7f221897-ef58-464f-8922-04b1cd3016cc"]}, "7f221897-ef58-464f-8922-04b1cd3016cc": {"id": "7f221897-ef58-464f-8922-04b1cd3016cc", "message": {"id": "7f221897-ef58-464f-8922-04b1cd3016cc", "author": {"role": "tool", "name": "file_search", "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191174.3913598, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["The files uploaded by the user in the current message have been fully loaded. Searching won't provide additional information from these specific files. However, remember that some of the previously uploaded files were not fully loaded, so you should invoke msearch to search their full content as needed."]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true, "reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "classifier_response": "default", "request_id": "97516821caab3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "model_slug": "gpt-5", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "6e21d8f5-a5c6-4570-bd82-73458609861c", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "6e21d8f5-a5c6-4570-bd82-73458609861c", "children": ["e558286f-94e0-403e-9471-dc203e6af75d"]}, "e558286f-94e0-403e-9471-dc203e6af75d": {"id": "e558286f-94e0-403e-9471-dc203e6af75d", "message": {"id": "e558286f-94e0-403e-9471-dc203e6af75d", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191178.929478, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "thoughts", "thoughts": [{"summary": "Analisando erro de permiss\u00e3o e awk", "content": "O erro no `awk` pode estar relacionado ao uso do `busybox awk`, que talvez espere uma sintaxe POSIX. Al\u00e9m disso, o script n\u00e3o est\u00e1 executando devido ao erro de permiss\u00e3o. Talvez o bit de execu\u00e7\u00e3o tenha se perdido ap\u00f3s a redire\u00e7\u00e3o `tee`. Tamb\u00e9m preciso verificar o caminho correto do shebang e se o sistema de arquivos tem a flag `noexec`.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Analisando erro de permiss\u00e3o e awk novamente", "content": "O erro pode ter ocorrido devido ao redirecionamento que sobrescreveu o arquivo e perdeu o bit de execu\u00e7\u00e3o. Vou precisar rodar `chmod +x` ap\u00f3s o hotfix. Tamb\u00e9m preciso corrigir o erro de `awk`, talvez relacionado ao uso de vari\u00e1veis ou \u00e0 sintaxe do `busybox awk`. Uma solu\u00e7\u00e3o seria usar `sed` em vez de `awk`.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}, {"summary": "Gerando o script corrigido", "content": "O usu\u00e1rio deseja o script completo v7_mod4 com as corre\u00e7\u00f5es. Vou gerar um bloco `cat > ... <<'SH'` com o script corrigido, incluindo o manuseio de APT e a inser\u00e7\u00e3o do SQLite via Python. Tamb\u00e9m fornecerei as instru\u00e7\u00f5es para adicionar permiss\u00f5es de execu\u00e7\u00e3o e validar o caminho do bash. Caso haja erro de permiss\u00e3o, sugerir o uso do bash diretamente.", "chunks": [], "finished": true}], "source_analysis_msg_id": "25e28253-b6f3-436c-a64f-4c5069bb1c29"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "is_reasoning", "citations": [], "content_references": [], "classifier_response": "default", "skip_reasoning_title": "Pular", "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "97516821caab3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "7f221897-ef58-464f-8922-04b1cd3016cc", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "7f221897-ef58-464f-8922-04b1cd3016cc", "children": ["f30377f4-9b10-4b4b-ae5c-9edefffae5c3"]}, "f30377f4-9b10-4b4b-ae5c-9edefffae5c3": {"id": "f30377f4-9b10-4b4b-ae5c-9edefffae5c3", "message": {"id": "f30377f4-9b10-4b4b-ae5c-9edefffae5c3", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191214.08609, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "reasoning_recap", "content": "Pensou por 39s"}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": false, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"reasoning_status": "reasoning_ended", "finished_duration_sec": 39, "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "97516821caab3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "e558286f-94e0-403e-9471-dc203e6af75d", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "e558286f-94e0-403e-9471-dc203e6af75d", "children": ["763617f7-cc8a-4255-9c82-cf5e37ff7a49"]}, "763617f7-cc8a-4255-9c82-cf5e37ff7a49": {"id": "763617f7-cc8a-4255-9c82-cf5e37ff7a49", "message": {"id": "763617f7-cc8a-4255-9c82-cf5e37ff7a49", "author": {"role": "assistant", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191170.680965, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["beleza \u2014 teu Termux reclamou de duas coisas:\n\n- o **awk** do patch (busybox) engasgou, apesar de ter escrito algo no arquivo;\n- o arquivo perdeu o bit de execu\u00e7\u00e3o, ent\u00e3o deu **Permission denied**.\n\nVamos cortar o n\u00f3 gordiano: te mando **o script inteiro j\u00e1 corrigido** (v7_mod4), com todos os hotfixes embutidos. \u00c9 s\u00f3 colar com `cat`, dar `chmod +x` e rodar.\n\n### 1) Gerar o arquivo (no telefone, direto no Termux)\n\n```bash\ncat > ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh <<'SH'\n#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash\n# RAFAELIA \u2014 UNO v7_mod4 (Android 14 / Termux modded-friendly)\n# subcmds: fix-apt | init | tune | headsupd {start|stop|status} | ingest | index | backup | mirror | run | help\nset -Eeuo pipefail\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 util \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nTS(){ date '+%F %T'; }\nsay(){ printf '%s %s\\n' \"$(TS)\" \"$*\"; }\nneed(){ command -v \"$1\" >/dev/null 2>&1 || { say \"[MISS] $1\"; return 1; }; }\n\n# Blocos livres (KB) port\u00e1til (toybox/busybox/coreutils)\nkb_free(){\n  if df -P \"$HOME\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n    df -P \"$HOME\" | awk 'NR==2{print $4}'\n    return\n  fi\n  if df \"$HOME\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n    df \"$HOME\" | awk 'NR==2{print $4}'\n    return\n  fi\n  echo 0\n}\nfree_mb(){ local k; k=\"$(kb_free)\"; printf '%s\\n' \"$(( k/1024 ))\"; }\nsha(){ sha256sum \"$1\" 2>/dev/null | awk '{print $1}'; }\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 paths/logs (fallback p/ sdcard se pouco espa\u00e7o) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nPREFIX=\"/data/data/com.termux/files/usr\"\nAPT=\"$PREFIX/etc/apt\"; SRC=\"$APT/sources.list.d\"; TRUST=\"$APT/trusted.gpg.d\"\nBASE=\"${BASE:-$HOME/FCEA_OMEGA}\"\nETC=\"$BASE/etc\"; BIN=\"$BASE/bin\"; DATA=\"$BASE/data\"; OUT=\"$BASE/out\"; BAK=\"$BASE/backups\"\nINBOX=\"$DATA/inbox\"; INDEX=\"$BASE/index\"\n\n_FREE=\"$(free_mb)\"\nif [ \"${_FREE:-0}\" -lt 200 ]; then\n  LOGDIR=\"/sdcard/rafaelia_logs\"\nelse\n  LOGDIR=\"$HOME/rafaelia_logs\"\nfi\nmkdir -p \"$LOGDIR\" \"$ETC\" \"$BIN\" \"$DATA\" \"$OUT\" \"$BAK\" \"$INBOX\" \"$INDEX\"\nLOG=\"$LOGDIR/uno_v7_mod4.log\"\nexec > >(tee -a \"$LOG\") 2>&1\nsay \"\u25b6 UNO v7_mod4 start (free=${_FREE:-?}MB logdir=$LOGDIR)\"\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 fix-apt (com import de chaves) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_fix_apt(){\n  say \"[APT] normalizando reposit\u00f3rios\u2026\"\n  local back=\"$APT/backup_fix_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)\"; mkdir -p \"$back\"\n  cp -a \"$SRC\" \"$back/\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  cp -a \"$TRUST\" \"$back/\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  say \"[backup] fontes/keyring \u2192 $back\"\n\n  # limpa .list antigos/duplicados\n  rm -f \"$SRC\"/*.list \"$SRC\"/*.list.bak \"$SRC\"/*legacy* 2>/dev/null || true\n  # chave \u00fanica\n  rm -f \"$TRUST/termux-main.gpg\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  pkg install -y gnupg curl ca-certificates termux-keyring || true\n\n  # fontes .sources com Signed-By unificado\n  cat > \"$SRC/termux-main.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://packages.termux.dev/apt/termux-main\nSuites: stable\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n  cat > \"$SRC/x11.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://x11-packages.termux.net\nSuites: x11\nComponents: main\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n  cat > \"$SRC/root.sources\" <<EOF\nTypes: deb\nURIs: https://root-packages.termux.net\nSuites: root\nComponents: stable\nSigned-By: $TRUST/termux.gpg\nEOF\n\n  # importa chaves que faltam\n  mkdir -p \"$TRUST\"\n  keys=( 5A897D96E57CF20C 1584981E6CDDB22D )\n  ks=( hkps://keyserver.ubuntu.com hkps://keys.openpgp.org )\n  for s in \"${ks[@]}\"; do\n    for k in \"${keys[@]}\"; do\n      gpg --keyserver \"$s\" --recv-keys \"$k\" >/dev/null 2>&1 || true\n    done\n  done\n  gpg --export \"${keys[@]}\" 2>/dev/null | gpg --dearmor > \"$TRUST/termux.gpg\" || true\n  chmod 644 \"$TRUST/termux.gpg\" || true\n\n  # refresh\n  apt-get clean || true\n  rm -rf \"$APT/lists/\"* 2>/dev/null || true\n\n  if ! apt-get -o Acquire::AllowInsecureRepositories=false update; then\n    say \"[APT] update falhou \u2014 desabilitando x11/root e tentando novamente\u2026\"\n    mv \"$SRC/x11.sources\" \"$SRC/x11.sources.off\" 2>/dev/null || true\n    mv \"$SRC/root.sources\" \"$SRC/root.sources.off\" 2>/dev/null || true\n    apt-get clean || true\n    rm -rf \"$APT/lists/\"* 2>/dev/null || true\n    apt-get -o Acquire::AllowInsecureRepositories=false update\n  else\n    # se assinou ok, reativa x11/root (se estavam off) e valida\n    [ -f \"$SRC/x11.sources.off\" ] && mv \"$SRC/x11.sources.off\" \"$SRC/x11.sources\"\n    [ -f \"$SRC/root.sources.off\" ] && mv \"$SRC/root.sources.off\" \"$SRC/root.sources\"\n    apt-get clean || true\n    rm -rf \"$APT/lists/\"* 2>/dev/null || true\n    apt-get -o Acquire::AllowInsecureRepositories=false update || true\n  fi\n  say \"[APT] ok (com chaves importadas).\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 init \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_init(){\n  say \"[INIT] deps + servi\u00e7os\u2026\"\n  pkg install -y termux-services || true\n  mkdir -p \"$PREFIX/var/service\" || true\n  sv-enable crond 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 1\n  sv up crond 2>/dev/null || true\n\n  pkg install -y coreutils findutils tar gzip xz-utils zip unzip p7zip \\\n                 gawk sed grep ripgrep sqlite sox ffmpeg util-linux \\\n                 python nodejs-lts file || true\n\n  command -v termux-setup-storage >/dev/null 2>&1 && termux-setup-storage || true\n  grep -q 'umask 077' \"$HOME/.bashrc\" 2>/dev/null || echo 'umask 077'>>\"$HOME/.bashrc\"\n  chmod -R go-rwx \"$BASE\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  say \"[INIT] ok. BASE=$BASE\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 tune (A14) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_tune(){\n  say \"[TUNE] Android 14\u2026\"\n  sub_init\n  local is_root=0\n  if command -v su >/dev/null 2>&1 && su -c id | grep -q \"uid=0\"; then is_root=1; fi\n\n  local ADB=\"$HOME/adb_once.sh\"\n  cat > \"$ADB\" <<'ADB'\n#!/system/bin/sh\ncmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux\ncmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux.api 2>/dev/null || true\nappops set com.termux RUN_ANY_IN_BACKGROUND allow 2>/dev/null || true\nappops set com.termux WAKE_LOCK allow 2>/dev/null || true\nsettings put global app_standby_enabled 0 2>/dev/null || true\n# heads-up pode exigir WRITE_SECURE_SETTINGS\nsettings put global heads_up_notifications_enabled 0 2>/dev/null || true\nADB\n  chmod +x \"$ADB\"\n  say \"[TUNE] gerado $ADB (use via ADB se sem root).\"\n\n  if [ \"$is_root\" -eq 1 ]; then\n    su -c \"cmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux\" || true\n    su -c \"cmd deviceidle whitelist + com.termux.api\" || true\n    su -c \"appops set com.termux RUN_ANY_IN_BACKGROUND allow\" || true\n    su -c \"appops set com.termux WAKE_LOCK allow\" || true\n    su -c \"settings put global heads_up_notifications_enabled 0\" || true\n    su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 1\" || true; sleep 0.2; su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 0\" || true\n    say \"[TUNE] ajustes root aplicados.\"\n  fi\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 heads-up cleaner \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_headsupd(){\n  local action=\"${1:-status}\"\n  local SVC=\"$PREFIX/var/service/heads-up-cleaner\"\n  case \"$action\" in\n    start)\n      mkdir -p \"$SVC\"\n      cat > \"$SVC/run\" <<'R'\n#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/bash\nset -Eeuo pipefail\nLOG=\"$HOME/rafaelia_logs/heads_up_cleaner.log\"; mkdir -p \"${LOG%/*}\"\nis_root(){ command -v su >/dev/null 2>&1 && su -c id | grep -q 'uid=0'; }\nif ! is_root; then\n  echo \"$(date '+%F %T') [WARN] sem root: efeito limitado\" >> \"$LOG\"\n  while :; do sleep 30; done\nfi\nwhile :; do\n  su -c \"cmd statusbar collapse-panels\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 1\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 0.2\n  su -c \"settings put global zen_mode 0\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 3\ndone\nR\n      chmod +x \"$SVC/run\"\n      sv-enable heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true\n      sleep 1\n      sv up heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true\n      say \"[HUN] daemon iniciado.\"\n      ;;\n    stop)   sv down heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true; sv-disable heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || true; say \"[HUN] parado.\";;\n    status) sv status heads-up-cleaner 2>/dev/null || { say \"[HUN] servi\u00e7o ausente\"; } ;;\n    *)      say \"uso: $0 headsupd {start|stop|status}\";;\n  esac\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 helper para INSERT robusto em SQLite \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\npy_insert(){\n  python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport sys,sqlite3,json\ndb=sys.argv[1]\nrec=json.loads(sys.stdin.read())\ncon=sqlite3.connect(db)\ncon.execute(\"PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL;\")\ncon.execute(\"\"\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS files(\n  path TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  size_bytes INTEGER,\n  sha256 TEXT,\n  kind TEXT,\n  extra TEXT,\n  json TEXT\n);\"\"\")\ncon.execute(\"INSERT OR REPLACE INTO files VALUES(?,?,?,?,?,?)\",(\n  rec[\"path\"], int(rec[\"size\"]), rec.get(\"sha256\",\"\"), rec.get(\"kind\",\"\"),\n  rec.get(\"extra\",\"\"), json.dumps(rec,ensure_ascii=False)\n))\ncon.commit(); con.close()\nPY\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 ingest (auto: copy/link; pula lixo oculto) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_ingest(){\n  say \"[INGEST] varrendo fontes\u2026\"\n  local globs=\"${SCAN_GLOBS:-/sdcard/Download/* /sdcard/*}\"\n  local mode=\"${INGEST_MODE:-auto}\"              # auto|copy|link\n  local cutoff_mb=\"${INGEST_CUTOFF_MB:-50}\"      # >=cutoff \u2192 link no auto\n  local count=0 dest f\n  mkdir -p \"$INBOX\"\n\n  local free=\"$(free_mb)\"\n  if [ \"$mode\" = \"auto\" ]; then\n    if [ \"${free:-0}\" -lt 512 ]; then mode=\"link\"; else mode=\"copy\"; fi\n  fi\n  say \"[INGEST] modo=$mode free=${free:-?}MB cutoff=${cutoff_mb}MB\"\n\n  shopt -s nullglob dotglob\n  for pattern in $globs; do\n    if [ -d \"$pattern\" ]; then\n      while IFS= read -r -d '' f; do\n        [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n        base=\"$(basename \"$f\")\"\n        [[ \"$base\" = .* ]] && continue\n        [[ \"$base\" = .trashed-* ]] && continue\n        dest=\"$INBOX/$base\"\n        if [ ! -e \"$dest\" ]; then\n          if [ \"$mode\" = \"link\" ] || [ $(( $(stat -c %s \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || stat -f %z \"$f\") / 1024 / 1024 )) -ge \"$cutoff_mb\" ]; then\n            ln -s -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true\n          else\n            cp -n -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true\n          fi\n        fi\n      done < <(find \"$pattern\" -maxdepth 1 -type f -print0 2>/dev/null)\n    else\n      for f in $pattern; do\n        [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n        base=\"$(basename \"$f\")\"\n        [[ \"$base\" = .* ]] && continue\n        [[ \"$base\" = .trashed-* ]] && continue\n        dest=\"$INBOX/$base\"\n        if [ ! -e \"$dest\" ]; then\n          if [ \"$mode\" = \"link\" ] || [ $(( $(stat -c %s \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || stat -f %z \"$f\") / 1024 / 1024 )) -ge \"$cutoff_mb\" ]; then\n            ln -s -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true\n          else\n            cp -n -- \"$f\" \"$dest\" && count=$((count+1)) || true\n          fi\n        fi\n      done\n    fi\n  done\n  shopt -u nullglob dotglob\n  say \"[INGEST] $count entradas (link/copy) \u2192 $INBOX\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 index (segue symlinks; insert via Python) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_index(){\n  say \"[INDEX] cat\u00e1logo profundo\u2026\"\n  local free=\"$(free_mb)\"; [ \"${free:-0}\" -lt 200 ] && { say \"[INDEX] abort: livre ${free}MB < 200MB\"; return 0; }\n  local CSV=\"$INDEX/index.csv\"; local JSON=\"$INDEX/index.jsonl\"; local SQL=\"$INDEX/index.sqlite\"; local LOGI=\"$INDEX/index.log\"\n  mkdir -p \"$INDEX\"; : > \"$JSON\"; : > \"$CSV\"; echo 'path,size_bytes,sha256,kind,extra,json' > \"$CSV\"\n  need sqlite3 || pkg install -y sqlite || true\n  sqlite3 \"$SQL\" 'PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL; CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS files(path TEXT PRIMARY KEY,size_bytes INTEGER,sha256 TEXT,kind TEXT,extra TEXT,json TEXT);'\n\n  list_zip(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport zipfile,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  with zipfile.ZipFile(p,'r') as z:\n    infos=[{'name':i.filename,'size':i.file_size,'comp':i.compress_size} for i in z.infolist() if not i.is_dir()]\n    print(json.dumps({'entries':len(infos),'top':infos[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  list_tar(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport tarfile,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  with tarfile.open(p,'r:*') as t:\n    names=[m.name for m in t.getmembers() if m.isfile()]\n    print(json.dumps({'entries':len(names),'top':names[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  list_sqlite(){ python - \"$1\" <<'PY'\nimport sqlite3,json,sys; p=sys.argv[1]\ntry:\n  con=sqlite3.connect(p); cur=con.cursor()\n  cur.execute(\"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table'\"); tabs=[r[0] for r in cur.fetchall()]\n  info={}\n  for t in tabs[:25]:\n    try: cur.execute(f\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM '{t}'\"); info[t]=cur.fetchone()[0]\n    except Exception as e: info[t]=str(e)\n  print(json.dumps({'tables':len(tabs),'counts':info,'sample':tabs[:25]}))\nexcept Exception as e:\n  print(json.dumps({'error':str(e)}))\nPY\n  }\n  summ(){ head -n \"${2:-12}\" \"$1\" 2>/dev/null | tr -d '\\r' | sed 's/\"/'\\''/g'; }\n\n  echo \"$(TS) [START] $INBOX \u2192 $INDEX\" | tee -a \"$LOGI\"\n  while IFS= read -r -d '' f; do\n    base=\"$(basename \"$f\")\"\n    [[ \"$base\" = .* ]] && continue\n    [[ \"$base\" = .trashed-* ]] && continue\n    size=$(stat -c %s \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || stat -f %z \"$f\")\n    h=$(sha \"$f\" || true)\n    ext=\"${f##*.}\"; ext=\"${ext,,}\"\n    case \"$ext\" in\n      zip) extra=$(list_zip \"$f\"); kind=\"zip\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"zip\",\"extra\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"zip\" \"$extra\");;\n      tar|gz|tgz|bz2|xz) extra=$(list_tar \"$f\"); kind=\"tar\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"tar\",\"extra\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"tar\" \"$extra\");;\n      db|sqlite|sqlite3) extra=$(list_sqlite \"$f\"); kind=\"sqlite\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"sqlite\",\"extra\":\"%s\",\"meta\":%s}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"sqlite\" \"$extra\");;\n      sh|py|js|json|md|txt|cfg|ini|yml|yaml) preview=$(summ \"$f\" 12 | sed 's/[[:cntrl:]]//g'); kind=\"text\"; extra=\"preview\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"text\",\"extra\":\"preview\",\"preview\":\"%s\"}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$preview\");;\n      *) kind=\"$(file -b --mime-type \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"?\")\"; extra=\"\"; json=$(printf '{\"path\":\"%s\",\"size\":%s,\"sha256\":\"%s\",\"kind\":\"%s\",\"extra\":\"\"}' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$kind\");;\n    esac\n    # CSV/JSONL\n    printf '%s,%s,%s,\"%s\",\"%s\",\"%s\"\\n' \"$f\" \"$size\" \"$h\" \"$kind\" \"${extra//\\\"/\\\"\\\"}\" \"${json//\\\"/\\\"\\\"}\" >> \"$CSV\"\n    printf '%s\\n' \"$json\" >> \"$JSON\"\n    # INSERT robusto\n    py_insert \"$SQL\" <<< \"$json\"\n  done < <(find -L \"$INBOX\" -type f -print0 2>/dev/null)\n  echo \"$(TS) [OK] CSV:$CSV JSONL:$JSON SQLITE:$SQL\" | tee -a \"$LOGI\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 backup \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_backup(){\n  say \"[BK] empacotando\u2026\"\n  local stamp=\"$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)\"\n  local bundle=\"$BAK/state_$stamp.zip\"\n  local mtmp=\"$OUT/manifest_runtime.json\"\n  mkdir -p \"$OUT\" \"$BAK\"\n  cat > \"$mtmp\" <<JSON\n{\n  \"run_at\":\"$(TS)\",\n  \"base\":\"$BASE\",\n  \"schema\":1,\n  \"paridade\":\"par\",\n  \"tesseract_hyperformas\":\"1 tesseract + 4 hyperformas\",\n  \"chave_simbiotica\":\"Fibonacci_mod + Voynich \ua66e-\u0394-\ud80c\udc80\"\n}\nJSON\n  ( cd \"$HOME\" && zip -qr \"$bundle\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$LOG\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$INDEX\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$OUT\")\" \\\n      \"$(realpath --relative-to=\"$HOME\" \"$mtmp\")\" \\\n  ) || true\n  say \"[BK] \u2192 $bundle\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 mirror (rclone) \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_mirror(){\n  if ! command -v rclone >/dev/null 2>&1; then say \"[SYNC] rclone ausente; pulando\"; return 0; fi\n  local conf=\"$HOME/.config/rclone/rclone.conf\"\n  if grep -q 'PREENCHER' \"$conf\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    say \"[SYNC] rclone.conf com placeholder; configure com 'rclone config'\"; return 0\n  fi\n  local DST=\"VAULT:FCEA_OMEGA\"; local DATE=\"$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\"\n  say \"[SYNC] $BASE \u2192 $DST/$DATE\"\n  rclone copy \"$BASE\" \"$DST/$DATE\" --fast-list --checkers=6 --transfers=6 --tpslimit=8 --log-level INFO || true\n  say \"[SYNC] ok.\"\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 run \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_run(){ say \"=== RUN in\u00edcio ===\"; sub_ingest; sub_index; sub_backup; sub_mirror; say \"=== RUN fim ===\"; }\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 help \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nsub_help(){\n  cat <<H\nuso: $0 <fix-apt|init|tune|headsupd {start|stop|status}|ingest|index|backup|mirror|run|help>\n\nfix-apt     \u2014 normaliza APT (Signed-By \u00fanico; importa chaves; desabilita x11/root se falhar)\ninit        \u2014 deps, servi\u00e7os (crond), hardening leve\ntune        \u2014 Android 14 tuning (gera adb_once.sh e aplica root se houver)\nheadsupd    \u2014 daemon anti heads-up\ningest      \u2014 coleta (copy/link) p/ $INBOX  [INGEST_MODE=auto|copy|link, INGEST_CUTOFF_MB=50]\nindex       \u2014 indexa\u00e7\u00e3o profunda (CSV/JSONL/SQLite) em $INDEX (segue symlinks; insert robusto)\nbackup      \u2014 bundle com manifesto simbi\u00f3tico em $BAK\nmirror      \u2014 rclone \u2192 VAULT:FCEA_OMEGA (se rclone.conf v\u00e1lido)\nrun         \u2014 ingest \u2192 index \u2192 backup \u2192 mirror\nH\n}\n\n# \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 main \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\ncmd=\"${1:-help}\"\ncase \"$cmd\" in\n  fix-apt)   sub_fix_apt;;\n  init)      sub_init;;\n  tune)      sub_tune;;\n  headsupd)  shift; sub_headsupd \"${1:-status}\";;\n  ingest)     sub_ingest;;\n  index)      sub_index;;\n  backup)     sub_backup;;\n  mirror)     sub_mirror;;\n  run)        sub_run;;\n  help|*)     sub_help;;\nesac\nSH\nchmod +x ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh\n```\n\n### 2) Se o sistema disser \u201cPermission denied\u201d de novo\n\u00c0s vezes, ao sobrescrever com `cat`, o bit de execu\u00e7\u00e3o cai. Recoloque:\n\n```bash\nchmod 700 ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh\n```\n\ne, se **ainda** negar (raro, mas se a parti\u00e7\u00e3o estiver `noexec`), invoque via shell:\n\n```bash\nbash ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh run\n```\n\n### 3) Sequ\u00eancia recomendada\n\n```bash\n# limpa inbox antiga (opcional)\nrm -f ~/FCEA_OMEGA/data/inbox/* 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# APT com chaves\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh fix-apt\n\n# Ambiente\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh init\n\n# Tuning Android 14\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh tune\n\n# Heads-up (opcional)\n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh headsupd start\n\n# Pipeline \u2014 auto (link para arquivos grandes/quando pouco espa\u00e7o)\nINGEST_MODE=auto INGEST_CUTOFF_MB=50 ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh run\n```\n\n### O que ficou resolvido\n- `df` port\u00e1til (nada de `-m`): sem \u201cUnknown option 'm'\u201d.\n- `apt` com **chaves importadas** e Signed-By \u00fanico (evita \u201cnot signed\u201d/duplicatas).\n- ingest **pula lixo oculto** (`.*`, `.trashed-*`) e faz **link** quando conv\u00e9m.\n- index **segue symlinks** e faz `INSERT` pelo Python (\u00e0 prova de paths \u201cdoidos\u201d).\n- se faltar espa\u00e7o em `/data`, logs j\u00e1 migram pro `/sdcard`.\n\nSe voc\u00ea quiser que eu **fa\u00e7a essas mesmas mudan\u00e7as dentro do arquivo can\u00f4nico** que voc\u00ea usa (ex.: `~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod2.sh` ou `~/FCEA_OMEGA.sh`), mando um patch \u201ccola-e-pronto\u201d espec\u00edfico para ele tamb\u00e9m."]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": true, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"citations": [], "content_references": [], "model_slug": "gpt-5-thinking", "request_id": "97516821caab3652-FLN", "message_type": "next", "default_model_slug": "gpt-5", "parent_id": "f30377f4-9b10-4b4b-ae5c-9edefffae5c3", "timestamp_": "absolute"}, "recipient": "all", "channel": "final"}, "parent": "f30377f4-9b10-4b4b-ae5c-9edefffae5c3", "children": ["ec0c7a1d-c7b0-4ed2-858c-42f84612d3eb"]}, "ec0c7a1d-c7b0-4ed2-858c-42f84612d3eb": {"id": "ec0c7a1d-c7b0-4ed2-858c-42f84612d3eb", "message": {"id": "ec0c7a1d-c7b0-4ed2-858c-42f84612d3eb", "author": {"role": "system", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191890.8402135, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": [""]}, "status": "finished_successfully", "end_turn": null, "weight": 1.0, "metadata": {"attachments": [{"id": "file-Fzi28rdbSfR3GVc8yeJFFt", "name": "JSON.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-1LhzSbDKvtcemqcxggHNY7", "name": "backup_20250528_005117.tar.gz", "mimeType": "application/gzip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-8n7eB6f8H7D7x96W7nSxW7", "name": "29ccc67a-7890-11f0-8b77-e00e72c952c1.tar.gz", "mimeType": "application/gzip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-VD69HBciWd3eS5zn8y6gXG", "name": "d6e9db90fbd5ffb1158e68518e6f46005d1c78dbaef56427bb8a934c8f466c0a-2025-06-29-04-43-33-cefe5cb372804d79a18d0829d4655fee.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-E6ex7Q5RDm3xeQedoB7bbi", "name": "abra_leia_e via m\u00e1quina a maquina tem todas Minhas intera\u00e7\u00f5es entao eh para ler via bit a bit nem precisa descompactar pois eh bit a bit consegue sim.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-PsQS6wFk69ULTTtGPXZWzz", "name": "mapa.txt", "mimeType": "text/plain", "fileSizeTokens": 1153374}, {"id": "file-M3w1cXMmP62NAUVGDaVUoP", "name": "todos_scripts.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}, {"id": "file-Dn8VGcAD9Ea9zvdhAnU636", "name": "RAIO_X_RafaelIA.txt", "mimeType": "text/plain", "fileSizeTokens": 627926}, {"id": "file-VV4nFMtPnuhQU4gtqFc4MG", "name": "rafaelia_simbiotico.zip", "mimeType": "application/zip", "fileSizeTokens": null}], "rebase_developer_message": true, "timestamp_": "absolute", "is_visually_hidden_from_conversation": true}, "recipient": "all", "channel": null}, "parent": "763617f7-cc8a-4255-9c82-cf5e37ff7a49", "children": ["bbb21fe6-d31e-42bb-9f6a-d37ffb630caa"]}, "bbb21fe6-d31e-42bb-9f6a-d37ffb630caa": {"id": "bbb21fe6-d31e-42bb-9f6a-d37ffb630caa", "message": {"id": "bbb21fe6-d31e-42bb-9f6a-d37ffb630caa", "author": {"role": "user", "name": null, "metadata": {}}, "create_time": 1756191890.889384, "update_time": null, "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["  \n# APT com chaves  \n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh fix-apt  \n  \n# Ambiente  \n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh init  \n  \n# Tuning Android 14  \n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh tune  \n  \n# Heads-up (opcional)  \n~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh headsupd start  \n  \n# Pipeline \u2014 auto (link para arquivos grandes/quando pouco espa\u00e7o)  \nINGEST_MODE=auto INGEST_CUTOFF_MB=50 ~/BLOCO_UNO_ABSOLUTO_v7_mod4.sh run  \n2025-08-26 04:03:19 \u25b6 UNO v7_mod4 start (free=9876MB logdir=/data/data/com.termux/files/home/rafaelia_logs)  \n2025-08-26 04:03:19 [APT] normalizando reposit\u00f3rios\u2026  \n2025-08-26 04:03:19 [backup] fontes/keyring \u2192 /data/data/com.termux/files/usr/etc/apt/backup_fix_20250826_040319  \n  \nWARNING: apt does not have a stable CLI interface. Use with caution in scripts.  \n  \nReading package lists...  \nBuilding dependency tree...  \nReading state information...  \ngnupg is already the newest version (2.5.11).  \ncurl is already the newest version (8.15.0-1).  \nca-certificates is already the newest version (1:2025.08.12).  \ntermux-keyring is already the newest version (3.15).  \nThe following package was automatically installed and is no longer required:  \n  mpg123  \nUse 'apt autoremove' to remove it.  \n  \nSummary:  \n  Upgrading: 0, Installing: 0, Removing: 0, Not Upgrading: 17  \n  \ngpg: no valid OpenPGP data found.  \nHit:1 https://root-packages.termux.net root InRelease  \nHit:2 https://x11-packages.termux.net x11 InRelease  \nErr:1 https://root-packages.termux.net root InRelease  \n  The following signatures couldn't be verified because the public key is not available: NO_PUBKEY 1584981E6CDDB22D  \nErr:2 https://x11-packages.termux.net x11 InRelease  \n  The following signatures couldn't be verified because the public key is not available: NO_PUBKEY 1584981E6CDDB22D  \nGet:3 https://packages.termux.dev/apt/termux-main stable InRelease [14.0 kB]  \nErr:3 https://packages.termux.dev/apt/termux-main stable InRelease  \n  The following signatures couldn't